Message.MsgText: INVALID_LOCAL_TRANSACTION_RESOLVER_CNTR0073E=CNTR0073E: Bean "{0}" attempted to use an invalid Local Transactions Resolution control.
Message.Explanation: The Local Transactions Resolution control must be ContainerAtBoundary for a container-managed transaction or a container-managed Activity Session.
Message.UserResponse: Set the Local Transactions Resolution control to "ContainerAtBoundary".

Message.MsgText: NON_APPLICATION_EXCEPTION_CNTR0018E=CNTR0018E: EJB threw an unexpected (non-declared) exception. Exception data: {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception, which is not declared on the EJB method signature, was created when the EJB container attempted to invoke an EJB method.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the origin of the exception. If the exception originates from customer-written code, correct the cause of the exception. If not, visit the IBM support Web site for information on problem determination.

Message.MsgText: NAME_ALREADY_BOUND_FOR_SAME_EJB_CNTR0173E=CNTR0173E: The {0} interface of the {1} bean in the {2} module of the {3} application cannot be bound to the {4} name location. The {5} interface of the same bean has already been bound to the {4} name location.
Message.Explanation: Each enterprise bean interface must specify a unique binding location.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the binding file for one of these two bean interfaces so that each interface has a unique binding location.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_PURGE_AUTOMATIC_TIMERS_CNTR0252W=CNTR0252W: Unable to remove automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers from the scheduler for the {0} application and {1} module, running on the {2} server. To remove the timers manually, use wsadmin to execute this command: $AdminTask removeAutomaticEJBTimers "-appName {0} -moduleName {1} -serverName {2} -nodeName {3} "
Message.Explanation: Any automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers associated with the application and module, on the server, were not removed from the scheduler. Therefore, the scheduler may attempt to run these timers in the future.
Message.UserResponse: Execute the 'removeAutomaticEJBTimers' command from a connected wsadmin session to remove the timers associated with the application and module on this specific server.

Message.MsgText: SECURITY_COLLABORATOR_THREW_UNEXPECTED_EXCEPTION_CNTR0017W=CNTR0017W: Security collaborator threw unexpected exception. Exception data: {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: DEFAULT_EJB_HOME_JNDI_NAME_CNTR0174I=CNTR0174I: The {0} bean in the {1} module is an Enterprise Java Beans (EJB) version prior to 3.0, and has no home binding name specified. The following binding name has been manufactured for this bean: {2}.
Message.Explanation: The home interface will be bound at the specified naming location.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: IOEXCEPTION_READING_FILE_FOR_STATEFUL_SESSION_BEAN_CNTR0024W=CNTR0024W: Unable to open input stream: {0} {1} {2}
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise Java Bean (EJB) container encountered an IOException while attempting to read a file for a stateful session bean.
Message.UserResponse: See the message in the IOException to determine the action to take. Ensure that the proper file permissions are set for the file.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SESSION_SYNCH_SIGNATURE_CNTR0327E=CNTR0327E: The {0} method does not have the required method signature for a {1} session synchronization method.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.1 specification requires that session synchronization methods of a stateful session bean class have the following signature: after-begin and before-completion : void <METHOD> (), after-completion : void <METHOD> (boolean)
Message.UserResponse: Correct the session synchronization method signature for this bean class.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9421E_INVALID_LTC_RESOLVER_PROPERTY=CNTR9421E: The {0} property was assigned an incorrect value of {1}. This property indicates the local transaction containment (LTC) resolver setting, and must be either Application (default) or ContainerAtBoundary.
Message.Explanation: The LTC resolver property was assigned an unsupported value.
Message.UserResponse: The LTC resolver property must be assigned a default value of Application or ContainerAtBoundary.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_TOKENBYTES_CNTR0107E=CNTR0107E: Method {0} cannot convert token to byte array : stoken = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The method that is specified was not able to convert the servant token to a byte array.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: SINGLETON_ACCESS_TIMEOUT_OVERFLOW_CNTR0196E=CNTR0196E: The conversion of access timeout value {0} from {1} time unit to milli-seconds time unit resulted in an overflow.
Message.Explanation: The access timeout is specified either via annotations or by deployment descriptor. The resulting conversion to milli-seconds must be greater than zero and less than java.lang.Long.MAX_VALUE (9223372036854775807) to be valid.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the access timeout value for the method identified by the message. A method name of "*" is used in deployment descriptor to indicate all methods of the singleton class. If annotation is used and @AccessTimeout annotation is not found on the method, correct the @AccessTimeout annotation at class level.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_PURGE_AUTOMATIC_TIMERS_CNTR0251W=CNTR0251W: Unable to remove automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers from the scheduler for the {0} application, running on the {1} server. To remove the timers manually, use wsadmin to execute this command: $AdminTask removeAutomaticEJBTimers "-appName {0} -serverName {1} -nodeName {2} "
Message.Explanation: Any automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers associated with the application, on the server, were not removed from the scheduler. Therefore, the scheduler may attempt to run these timers in the future.
Message.UserResponse: Execute the 'removeAutomaticEJBTimers' command from a connected wsadmin session to remove the timers associated with the application on this specific server.

Message.MsgText: JIT_NO_EJBCREATE_METHOD_CNTR5026E=CNTR5026E: The {2} method of the {1} home interface for the {0} entity bean does not define a corresponding ejbCreate method for the {3} class.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the entity bean class must implement an ejbCreate method for every create method for a home interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bean class to provide an ejbCreate method that corresponds to the method.

Message.MsgText: BMT_DEFINES_CMT_ATTRIBUTES_CNTR0067W=CNTR0067W: SessionBean "{0}" or its home attempted to use an invalid combination of Bean Managed Transactions and Container Managed method-level transaction attributes. The method-level transaction attributes will be ignored.
Message.Explanation: The enterprise Java bean (EJB) specification states that a session bean or the home of a session bean with "Bean Managed Transactions" must not declare transaction attributes for the method. The attributes for the Container Managed method-level transaction have no meaning, because the session bean will use Bean Managed Transactions.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the transaction attributes for the methods of this bean or the bean home.

Message.MsgText: INPUT_FILE_NOT_FOUND_CNTR9265E=CNTR9265E: The {0} input file was not found.
Message.Explanation: The file specified as the first parameter was not found.
Message.UserResponse: Check the spelling and the read permissions of the specified file.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_LOCAL_TRANSACTION_RESOLVER_CNTR0071E=CNTR0071E: Bean "{0}" in an EJB 1.1 module attempted to use an invalid Local Transactions Resolution control of "ContainerAtBoundary".
Message.Explanation: Local Transactions Resolution control, "ContainerAtBoundary", is not supported for EJB V1.1 modules.
Message.UserResponse: Select "Application" for the Local Transactions Resolution control.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9410I_STOP=CNTR9410I: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container has closed.
Message.Explanation: The Close method has been invoked and the embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container has completed its shutdown routine.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_GET_WRAPPER_CNTR0056W=CNTR0056W: Failed to get the wrapper for a bean. Bean: {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: PARTIAL_CLASS_INTERCEPTOR_ORDER_CNTR0227E=CNTR0227E: The {0} enterprise bean has an interceptor-order element which specifies the following interceptor-order list: {1}. This list is not a total ordering of the class-level interceptors for this bean. It is missing the following interceptor names: {2}
Message.Explanation: When the interceptor-order element is used, the specified ordering at the class-level must be a total order. The order must be over all of the interceptor classes that have been defined at that level and above. The only exception to this rule is when interceptor classes have been explicitly excluded by means of an exclude-default-inteceptors element.
Message.UserResponse: Specify additional interceptor names on the class-level interceptor-order element for this bean. Then, the bean will provide a total ordering of the interceptors.

Message.MsgText: SINGLETON_DEPENDS_ON_NON_SINGLETON_BEAN_CNTR0200E=CNTR0200E: The {0} singleton session bean in the {1} module depends on the {2} enterprise bean in the {3} module, but the target is not a singleton session bean.
Message.Explanation: The bean was configured to depend on another bean through the @DependsOn annotation or the depends-on element in the ejb-jar.xml file. However, the other bean is not a singleton.
Message.UserResponse: Remove or change the dependency on the non-singleton bean, or adjust the type of the non-singleton bean.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_SF_HOME_METHOD_CNTR5023E=CNTR5023E: The {1} home interface for the {0} bean has a method that does not start with the create string. The {2} method is not allowed.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, all methods that are defined on a home interface for a stateless session bean must start with the create string.
Message.UserResponse: Change the name of the method on the home interface so that it starts with the create string, or remove the method.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_EJBFIND_RETURN_CNTR5031E=CNTR5031E: The {2} method with the {3} return type on the {1} class for the {0} entity bean must return the {4} primary key class.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the return type of the ejbFindByPrimaryKey method for an entity bean class must be the primary key type.
Message.UserResponse: Change the return type of the method to the primary key class.

Message.MsgText: JIT_NO_DEFAULT_CTOR_CNTR5007E=CNTR5007E: The {1} bean class for the {0} bean does not have a public constructor that does not take parameters.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the bean class must have a public constructor that does not take parameters.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bean class to have a public constructor that does not take parameters.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_PURGE_TIMERS_BECAUSE_RUNNING_IN_LOCAL_MODE_CNTR0254W=CNTR0254W: The application or module that was updated or removed contained automatically created Enterprise Java Bean timers. However, because processing ran in a local mode, the timers were not removed. Use the removeAutomaticEJBTimers command to remove them manually.
Message.Explanation: Use the removeAutommaticEJBTimers command to manually remove any automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers that are no longer valid.
Message.UserResponse: The processing to remove automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers does not execute when you are running in a disconnected wsadmin session. As a result, the automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers were not removed.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_ABSTRACT_CLASS_CNTR5005E=CNTR5005E: The {1} bean class for the {0} bean is defined as abstract.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the bean class must not be defined as abstract.
Message.UserResponse: Do not define the bean class as an abstract class.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_MSGDESTREF_BINDING_CNTR0091W=CNTR0091W: A reference to a MessageDestinationRef could not be found in the deployment descriptor for the WebApp or EnterpriseBean with the display name {0}.
Message.Explanation: The Java Enterprise Edition (Java EE) component might have specified binding information that is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the binding information is correct in the deployment descriptor for the Java EE component.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9416E_NO_DATASOURCECLASS_SPECIFIED=CNTR9416E: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container properties for the {0} data source do not contain the property, className.
Message.Explanation: The properties that the embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container uses contain a data source with no className specified.
Message.UserResponse: Add a className property for this data source to the properties file.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_BMP_HOME_METHOD_CNTR5024E=CNTR5024E: The {1} home interface for the {0} bean has a method that starts with the remove string. The {2} method is not allowed.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, you cannot define methods on an entity bean home interface that start with the remove string.
Message.UserResponse: Change the name of the method on the home interface so that it does not start with the remove string, or remove the method.

Message.MsgText: TIMEOUT_METHOD_MISSING_REQUIRED_PARM_CNTR0158E=CNTR0158E: The {0} session bean in the {1} module has the {2} method configured as a timeout method. This method must have a single parameter of the javax.ejb.Timer type, or take zero parameters.
Message.Explanation: Timer beans must implement a timeout method, which has either a single parameter of the javax.ejb.Timer type, or no parameters.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the bean implementation to include the required parameter, or include no parameters. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: CAUGHT_EXCEPTION_AND_RETHROWING_CNTR0039E=CNTR0039E: EJB container caught {0} and is rethrowing the caught exception.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_EXCEPTOKEN_CNTR0105E=CNTR0105E: Method {0} caught exception: {1} stoken = {2}.
Message.Explanation: The method that is specified caught an exception when processing the servant token.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: SERVICEREF_BINDING_EXCEPTION_CNTR0090E=CNTR0090E: WebServiceRef binding failed for {0} : {1}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SESSION_SYNCH_PARAM_CNTR0324E=CNTR0324E: The {0} method configured in the ejb-jar.xml file does not have the required method signature for a {1} session synchronization method for the {2} bean in the {3} module of the {4} application.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.1 specification requires that session synchronization methods of a stateful session bean class have the following signature: after-begin and before-completion : void <METHOD> (), after-completion : void <METHOD> (boolean)
Message.UserResponse: Correct the session synchronization method signature for this bean class.

Message.MsgText: TIMEOUT_METHOD_THROWS_APP_EXCEPTION_CNTR0164E=CNTR0164E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module implements a {2} timeout method, which creates an application exception..
Message.Explanation: Timeout methods must not create application exceptions.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the timeout method implementation to not create application exceptions. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_ACTIVATE_STATEFUL_BEAN_CNTR0003W=CNTR0003W: A Stateful SessionBean could not be activated: {0} {1} {2}
Message.Explanation: The container failed to activate a stateful session bean from storage.
Message.UserResponse: Take action based upon the exception message in message CNTR0003W.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MDB_INTERFACE_SPECIFIED_CNTR0134E=CNTR0134E: The {0} message-driven bean in the {1} module has an interface configured for a component, business, Web service endpoint, or home.
Message.Explanation: Message-driven beans cannot have any of these interface types configured.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file or source code annotation configuration settings for this bean.

Message.MsgText: JIT_MUST_EXTEND_EJBLOCALHOME_CNTR5016E=CNTR5016E: The {1} interface, which has been configured as the local home interface for the {0} bean, must extend the javax.ejb.EJBLocalHome interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the configured local home interface must extend the javax.ejb.EJBLocalHome interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the interface to extend the javax.ejb.EJBLocalHome interface or change the bean configuration to not specify the interface as a local home interface.

Message.MsgText: JIT_MISSING_REMOTE_EX_CNTR5104E=CNTR5104E: The {0} method on the {1} interface must be defined with the java.rmi.RemoteException exception on the throws clause.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, for remote business interface methods that implement the java.rmi.Remote interface, the throws clause must include the java.rmi.RemoteException exception.
Message.UserResponse: Add the RemoteException exception to the throws clause of the method. Also, you can change the interface to not implement the java.rmi.Remote interface or change the application to not use the interface as an EJB remote interface.

Message.MsgText: CLIENT_INACTIVITY_TIMEOUT_CNTR0051E=CNTR0051E: Transaction has timed out due to no client activity for greater than {1} seconds. Transaction ID: {0}
Message.Explanation: The client has been inactive longer than the inactivity timeout value.
Message.UserResponse: This can be a normal occurrence if client goes away and leaves a transaction active. If client is still active, have an administrator determine whether to change the Client or the Transaction Inactivity Timeout value.

Message.MsgText: LRU_THREAD_INTERRUPTED_CNTR0052W=CNTR0052W: LRU thread was interrupted. Terminating. {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: FBF_DISABLED_CNTR0098I=CNTR0098I: Container-managed pre-find persistent store synchronization disabled for bean: "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The application is configured for this bean to not synchronize with persistent storage prior to the invocation of custom findBy methods. This behavior is not compliant with the enterprise Java bean (EJB) V2.0 and later specifications, but it can improve performance.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: FINDER_ON_BEAN_NOT_SUPPORTED_CNTR0036E=CNTR0036E: EJB container does not support using the bean instance for finder methods on EJB 1.x container managed persistence and is throwing {0}
Message.Explanation: A bean that is configured for enterprise Java bean (EJB) V1.x container managed persistence has attempted to invoke methods on a bean instance for the processing of a finder method.
Message.UserResponse: Redeploy the bean and attempt the operation again.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_ROLES_SPECIFIED_IN_CLASS_ANNOTATION_CNTR0153E=CNTR0153E: The {0} role is specified multiple times in the class level @RolesAllowed annotation on the {1} enterprise bean class.
Message.Explanation: A given role can be specified once in a @RolesAllowed annotation..
Message.UserResponse: Change the Java source code by removing the duplicate roles from this annotation. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: SINGLETON_DEPENDS_ON_AMBIGUOUS_NAME_CNTR0199E=CNTR0199E: The {0} singleton session bean in the {1} module depends on {2}, which does not uniquely specify an enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: The bean was configured to depend on another bean with the specified name. A bean with that name does not exist in the same module, and more than one module has a bean with that name.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the dependency, or use a fully qualified bean name such as module.jar#BeanName

Message.MsgText: INTERCEPTOR_METHOD_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0238E=CNTR0238E: The {2} interceptor class specifies the {1} method, which is not an {0} method of this class.
Message.Explanation: The specified method name is not a method of the interceptor class.
Message.UserResponse: Correct either the method name or method signature to specify one of the methods of this interceptor class.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_EJBREF_BINDING_CNTR0063W=CNTR0063W: A reference to an EJB could not be found in the deployment descriptor for the WebApp or EnterpriseBean with the display name {0}. The EJB may have specified binding information that is not valid.
Message.Explanation: There might be a deployment descriptor with syntax that is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the binding information in the deployment descriptor for the enterprise Java bean (EJB) is correct.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9417E_MAXCONNECTIONS_VALUE_NOT_NUMERIC=CNTR9417E: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container properties for the {0} data source contain a {1} ConnectionPool.MaxConnections value that is not a positive numeric value or zero.
Message.Explanation: The properties that the embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container uses contain a data source with a ConnectionPool.MaxConnections value that is not a positive numeric value or zero.
Message.UserResponse: Change the ConnectionPool.MaxConnections property value for this data source to be a positive numeric value or zero.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9419E_JPA_CLOSE_FAIL=CNTR9419E: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container failed to shutdown the JPA provider. Exception: {0}
Message.Explanation: An error during shutdown processing prevented the JPA provider from closing correctly due to the exception. This is indicative of another problem that should have occurred earlier in the logs. Future attempts to use JPA may fail.
Message.UserResponse: Resolve the failure by examining the exception, the logs, and the FFDC output to find and resolve the underlying problem.

Message.MsgText: MAXIMUM_UNCLAIMED_ASYNC_RESULTS_CNTR0328W=CNTR0328W: There are {0} unclaimed results from remote asynchronous EJB method invocations. The product will discard the oldest result when the number of unclaimed results exceeds {1}.
Message.Explanation: The number of unretrieved results from remote asynchronous EJB method invocations is approaching or has exceeded the maximum. When the number of unretrieved results exceeds the maximum, the product will discard the oldest result.
Message.UserResponse: Monitor the AsyncFutureObjectCount PMI statistic to determine which EJB results have unclaimed results, and then update the corresponding client code to claim the results. If results are being discarded faster than clients can claim them, then adjust the remote future object duration for EJB asynchronous methods, and set the com.ibm.websphere.ejbcontainer.maxUnclaimedAsyncResults system property to the desired maximum number of unclaimed results. Alternatively, change the EJB to use a local interface rather than a remote interface since the results of an asynchronous method on a local interface do not need to be tracked by the EJB container and can be garbage collected normally.

Message.MsgText: JIT_MISSING_REMOTE_HOME_CNTR5001E=CNTR5001E: The {0} bean is configured with the {1} remote component interface, but a remote home interface has not been provided.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, a remote home interface must be provided when a remote component interface is provided.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application configuration to provide a remote home interface for the bean.

Message.MsgText: REQUIRED_INTERFACE_MISSING_CNTR0131E=CNTR0131E: The {0} bean in the {1} module does not have any configured productive interfaces.
Message.Explanation: Depending on the bean type, an enterprise bean must have at least one component, business, Web service endpoint, or message listener interface configured.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file or source code annotation configuration settings for this bean.

Message.MsgText: MULTIPLE_SESSION_SYNCH_METHODS_CNTR0326E=CNTR0326E: Multiple {0} session synchronization methods have been configured for the {1} bean. The configured session synchronization methods are : {2} and {3}
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.1 specification requires that only one of each type of session synchronization method be configured for a stateful session bean.
Message.UserResponse: Configure only one of each type of session synchronization method for this bean.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_TEMP_FILE_CNTR9261E=CNTR9261E: Unable to create temporary file in the {0} directory.
Message.Explanation: A temporary file could not be created on the file system.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the file system permissions settings for the specified directory.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_DELETE_ROOT_DIRECTORY_FOR_STUBS_PROCESSING_CNTR9271E=CNTR9271E: The {0} directory could not be deleted.
Message.Explanation: The specified directory can not be deleted.
Message.UserResponse: Manually delete the directory.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_INIT_ANNOTATION_CNTR0234E=CNTR0234E: An initialization method for a stateful session bean can be an ejbCreate<METHOD> method only when the bean conforms to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) 2.1 or earlier specification levels. Therefore, it cannot be applied to the {0} method of the {1} enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification requires a matching ejbCreate<METHOD> to be the initialization method of a stateful session bean class. This requirement exists for stateful session beans that are written for the EJB 2.1 or earlier-level application programming interface (API).
Message.UserResponse: Remove the @Init annotation or the init-method element in ejb-jar.xml file from the specified method of this bean.

Message.MsgText: NO_CONNECTION_FACTORY_FOR_CMP_BEAN_CNTR0148E=CNTR0148E: The {0} Container Managed Persistence (CMP) entity bean is configured to use a CMP Connection Factory with a {1} Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI). This Connection Factory resource is not configured.
Message.Explanation: The Connection Factory resource that is required by this bean is not configured. The CMP entity bean will not function.
Message.UserResponse: Create the required Connection Factory resource by ensuring that the proper data source is selected for CMP use in the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: STATEFUL_TIMEOUT_ON_NON_SFSB_CNTR0304W=CNTR0304W: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module of the {2} application contains the @StatefulTimeout annotation. The StatefulTimeout annotation is only valid on stateful session beans. The Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) container will ignore the annotation on this bean.
Message.Explanation: The @StatefulTimeout annotation is only applicable to stateful session beans. The Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) container will ignore the annotation on this bean.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the @StatefulTimeout annotation from the specified bean, or make the bean a stateful session bean.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SINGLETON_COMPONENT_INTERFACE_SPECIFIED_CNTR0320E=CNTR0320E: The {0} singleton session bean in the {1} module has an interface configured for a component view.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the EJB 2.1 remote and local client views are not supported for singleton session beans.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file or source code annotation configuration settings for this bean.

Message.MsgText: TIMERSERVICE_NOT_AVAILABLE_CNTR0080E=CNTR0080E: EJB timer service is not available for EJB implementing the javax.ejb.TimedObject interface: {0}.
Message.Explanation: The enterprise Java bean (EJB) implementation requires the EJB timer service, which has been disabled or did not start.
Message.UserResponse: See the previous messages to determine why the EJB timer service did not start, and correct the problem or enable the EJB timer service.

Message.MsgText: JIT_NON_PUBLIC_CLASS_CNTR5003E=CNTR5003E: The {1} bean class for the {0} bean is not defined as public.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the bean class must be defined as public.
Message.UserResponse: Define the bean class as public.

Message.MsgText: CONFIGURED_TIMEOUT_METHOD_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0162E=CNTR0162E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has specified the following timeout method: {2} This method is not implemented by the bean.
Message.Explanation: Timer beans must provide an implementation for the configured timeout method.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the bean implementation to include the required timeout method. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_FINAL_CLASS_CNTR5004E=CNTR5004E: The {1} bean class for the {0} bean is defined as final.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the bean class must not be defined as final.
Message.UserResponse: Do not define the bean class as a final class.

Message.MsgText: NO_REMOTE_INTERFACES_CNTR9241I=CNTR9241I: The {0} Java archive (JAR) file has no level 3.0 enterprise beans with remote interfaces.
Message.Explanation: The listed jar file does not contain any level 3.0 enterprise beans with remote interfaces.
Message.UserResponse: If this module should have contained level 3.0 enterprise beans with remote interfaces, check the module's annotations or ejb-jar.xml configuration data.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_EXTENDS_JAVAX_EJB_CNTR5012E=CNTR5012E: The {1} interface, which has been configured as a business interface for the {0} bean, must not extend the {2} interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the configured business interfaces must not extend any interface in the javax.ejb package.
Message.UserResponse: Change the business interface to not extend an interface in the javax.ejb package. Also, you can change the bean configuration to not specify the interface as a business interface.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_EXCEPTION_CNTR0100E=CNTR0100E: Method {0} caught exception: {1}
Message.Explanation: An exception was caught in the specified method.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: NON_APPLICATION_EXCEPTION_ON_BEAN_CNTR0021E=CNTR0021E: EJB threw an unexpected (non-declared) exception while invoking a method on bean "{1}". Exception data: {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception, which is not declared on the EJB method signature, was created when the EJB container attempted to invoke this EJB method.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the origin of the exception. If the exception originates from customer-written code, correct the cause of the exception. If not, visit the IBM support Web site for information on problem determination.

Message.MsgText: CUSTOMFINDER_SQLFORUPDATE_CNTR0078I=CNTR0078I: Custom Finder access intent support enabled for bean {0}
Message.Explanation: The user has specified that Custom Finders access intent must be honored. If the method has an Update access intent, the Access Intent will be honored.
Message.UserResponse: You can disable the processing of access intent for custom finders by using the Java Virtual Machine (JVM) and the properties at the bean level, or you can set the access intent of the method to Read-Only.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9422E_INVALID_LTC_UNRESOLVED_ACTION_PROPERTY=CNTR9422E: The {0} property was assigned an incorrect value of {1}. This property indicates the local transaction containment (LTC) unresolved action setting, and must be either Rollback (default) or Commit.
Message.Explanation: The LTC unresolved action property was assigned an unsupported value.
Message.UserResponse: The LTC unresolved action property must be assigned a default value of Rollback or Commit.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_DRSEVENT_IS_CONGESTED_CNTR0115I=CNTR0115I: SfDRSControllerInstance {0} received event IS_CONGESTED.
Message.Explanation: The SfDRSControllerInstance that is specified received the event IS_CONGESTED.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: CREATE_ENDPOINT_FAILED_CNTR0083E=CNTR0083E: Creation of a message endpoint failed: {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: TIMEOUT_METHOD_MUST_RETURN_VOID_CNTR0165E=CNTR0165E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module implements a {2} timeout method, which has a non-void return type.
Message.Explanation: Timeout methods must return void.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the timeout method implementation to return void. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_MTHD_PREFIX_CNTR5010E=CNTR5010E: The name of the {2} business method of the {1} interface for the {0} bean must not start with ejb.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the name of business methods must not start with ejb. Otherwise, conflicts might occur with the callback methods.
Message.UserResponse: Change the name of the business method so that it does not start with ejb.

Message.MsgText: ML_DUPLICATES_CL_CNTR0221E=CNTR0221E: The {0} method-level interceptor for the {1} method of the {2} enterprise bean duplicates a name that is in the following class-level interceptor list: {3}
Message.Explanation: An interceptor class can be either a class-level or a method-level interceptor, but not both types.
Message.UserResponse: Eliminate the interceptor class from either the class-level interceptor list or the method-level interceptor list.

Message.MsgText: STATEFUL_BEAN_REAPER_THREAD_INTERRUPTED_CNTR0014W=CNTR0014W: StatefulBeanReaper thread was interrupted; terminating. {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: TIMERSERVICE_TIMERMANAGER_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0183E=CNTR0183E: The timer manager used by the EJB timer service could not be obtained. {0}
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to obtain the timer manager, because the option to create a separate thread pool for non-persistent timers was configured on the EJBTimer configuration object (uniqueTimerManagerForNP).
Message.UserResponse: As an alternative, you may configure the timer service to use a scheduler for non-persistent timers.

Message.MsgText: REMOVE_FROM_PASSIVATION_STORE_FAILED_CNTR0016W=CNTR0016W: Passivated Stateful SessionBean "{0}" could not be removed due to exception: {1}
Message.Explanation: The container was unable to remove a passivated stateful session bean from the passivation store.
Message.UserResponse: Take action based upon the exception message in message CNTR0016W.

Message.MsgText: BOTH_SESSION_SYNCH_STYLES_CNTR0323E=CNTR0323E: The {0} bean in the {1} module of the {2} application implements the javax.ejb.SessionSynchronization interface and also configures a session synchronization method in the ejb-jar.xml or with an annotation. The configured session synchronization method is {3}.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.1 specification requires that a stateful session bean must not both implement the javax.ejb.SessionSynchronization interface and also configure a session synchronization method in the ejb-jar.xml file or with an annotation.
Message.UserResponse: Remove either the implementation of the javax.ejb.SessionSynchronization interface or the configuration of the session synchronization methods.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_LOG_FILE_PARAM_CNTR9255E=CNTR9255E: The required log file name parameter is missing.
Message.Explanation: For option -logfile, the log file name must be provided as the next parameter
Message.UserResponse: Examine the usage statement and provide the required log file name parameter.

Message.MsgText: BUSINESS_METHOD_NOT_FOUND_FOR_INTERCEPTOR_BINDING_CNTR0244E=CNTR0244E: The {0} method name is not found in one of the business interfaces of the {1} enterprise bean. A style {2} interceptor-binding element requires the method to be a business method of the enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, a style 3 or style 4 interceptor-binding must use a <method-name> tag to specify the name of a method that is found in one of the business interfaces of the enterprise bean.
Message.UserResponse: Either specify one of the method names found in one of the business interfaces of the enterprise bean or add the method to one of the business interfaces of the enterprise bean.

Message.MsgText: ENGLISH_ONLY_ERROR_MESSAGE_CNTR8992E=CNTR8992E: This message is an English-only Error message: {0}.
Message.Explanation: This error message is not translated.
Message.UserResponse: See message for details.

Message.MsgText: OUTPUT_FILE_NOT_FOUND_CNTR9272E=CNTR9272E: The {0} output file cannot be found.
Message.Explanation: The specified output file cannot be found.
Message.UserResponse: Check the spelling and the write permissions for the file.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_EVENT_CNTR0109E=CNTR0109E: Method {0} event parameter is null.
Message.Explanation: The method that is specified was passed an event parameter that is null.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: JNDI_BINDING_HAS_NO_CORRESPONDING_BUSINESS_INTERFACE_CLASS_CNTR0140E=CNTR0140E: The {0} bean in the {1} module has specified the {2} business interface, which does not exist for a business interface Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) binding.
Message.Explanation: Each business interface JNDI binding must have a valid business interface class configured.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file or source code annotations to configure a valid business interface class.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TX_ATTRIBUTE_FOR_ASYNCH_METHOD_CNTR0187E=CNTR0187E: The {0} method on the {1} bean in the {2} module of the {3} application has a {4} transaction attributed configured. Asynchronous methods only support transaction attributes of type TX_REQUIRED, TX_REQUIRES_NEW, or TX_NOT_SUPPORTED.
Message.Explanation: Asynchronous methods can have the following transaction attribute types configured: TX_REQUIRED, TX_REQUIRES_NEW, or TX_NOT_SUPPORTED.
Message.UserResponse: Change the transaction attribute configuration on the method to one of the three supported types.

Message.MsgText: INCOMPATIBLE_RETURN_TYPES_CNTR0322W=CNTR0322W: The {0} return type for the {1} method of the {2} enterprise bean is not compatible with the {3} return type for the corresponding method on the {4} interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, method return types for an enterprise bean must be compatible with the corresponding interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the return type of the method so that the enterprise bean and the interface return types are compatible.

Message.MsgText: PREPARED_STATEMENT_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0037E=CNTR0037E: Prepared statement does not map to connection.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_EXTENDS_REMOTE_CNTR5013E=CNTR5013E: The {1} interface, which has been configured as a local interface for the {0} bean, must not extend the javax.rmi.Remote interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the configured local interfaces must not extend the javax.rmi.Remote interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the interface to not extend the javax.rmi.Remote interface. Also, you can change the bean configuration to not specify the interface as a local interface.

Message.MsgText: ATTEMPT_TO_ACQUIRE_LOCK_INTERRUPTED_CNTR0004E=CNTR0004E: An attempt to acquire a lock was interrupted. Lock : {0}
Message.Explanation: A thread attempting to acquire an exclusive lock within the container was interrupted while waiting for the lock.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED_CNTR0047E=CNTR0047E: Bean is attempting to use interface or method "{0}" in a situation prohibited by the EJB specification.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise Java Bean (EJB) Specification does not allow the method for one of the following reasons: - The getRollbackOnly and setRollbackOnly methods of the MessageDriven-Context interface should be used only in the message-driven bean methods that run in the context of a transaction. # - Invoking the getCallerPrincipal and isCallerInRole methods is not allowed in the message-driven bean methods because the Container does not have a client security context. # - Invoking the getRollbackOnly and setRollbackOnly methods is not allowed in the message-driven bean methods for which the Container does not have a meaningful transaction context, and for all message-driven beans with bean-managed transaction demarcation. # - The UserTransaction interface is not available to message-driven beans with container- managed transaction demarcation. # - Invoking getEJBHome or getEJBLocalHome is not allowed in message-driven bean methods because there are no EJBHome or EJBLocalHome objects for message-driven beans. #
Message.UserResponse: Do not invoke the method in this environment.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_STYLE_3_INTERCEPTOR_BINDING_CNTR0247E=CNTR0247E: More than one style 3 interceptor-binding element is provided in the deployment descriptor for the {0} method of the {1} enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, only one style 3 interceptor-binding can be used for each method of an enterprise bean.
Message.UserResponse: Correct deployment descriptor so that only one style 3 interceptor-binding is used for the method of an enterprise bean.

Message.MsgText: INCOMPATIBLE_RETURN_TYPES_CNTR0321E=CNTR0321E: The {0} return type for the {1} method of the {2} enterprise bean does not match the {3} return type for the corresponding method on the {4} interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, method return types for an enterprise bean must match the corresponding interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the return type of the method so that the enterprise bean and the interface return types are the same.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_REMOVE_CNTR0008W=CNTR0008W: A passivated Stateful SessionBean could not be removed: {0} {1} {2}
Message.Explanation: The container was unable to remove a passivated stateful session bean from storage.
Message.UserResponse: Take action based upon the exception message in message CNTR0008W.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_DRSEVENT_NOT_CONGESTED_CNTR0116I=CNTR0116I: SfDRSControllerInstance {0} received event NOT_CONGESTED.
Message.Explanation: The SfDRSControllerInstance that is specified received the event NOT_CONGESTED.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_GET_WRAPPER_FOR_HOME_CNTR0002W=CNTR0002W: Failed to get the wrapper for a home. Home: {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MULTIPLE_JNDI_BINDING_NAMES_CNTR0139E=CNTR0139E: The {0} bean in the {1} module has multiple Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) binding names specified for the {2} business interface.
Message.Explanation: Each business interface can have a single JNDI binding name configured.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar-bnd.xml bindings file to give this bean a single JNDI binding name.

Message.MsgText: JIT_MUST_EXTEND_EJBOBJECT_CNTR5015E=CNTR5015E: The {1} interface, which has been configured as the remote component interface for the {0} bean, must extend the javax.ejb.EJBObject interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the configured remote component interface must extend the javax.ejb.EJBObject interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the interface to extend the javax.ejb.EJBObject interface. Also, you can change the bean configuration to not specify the interface as a remote component interface.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SESSION_BEAN_INTERFACE_SPECIFIED_CNTR0132E=CNTR0132E: The {0} session bean in the {1} module has an interface configured for a message listener or Web service endpoint.
Message.Explanation: Stateless session beans cannot have message listener interfaces configured. Stateful session beans cannot have either of these interface types configured.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file or source code annotation configuration settings for this bean.

Message.MsgText: UNEXPECTED_EXCEPTION_CNTR0188E=CNTR0188E: An unexpected exception was caught. The exception is: {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MISSING_CONTAINER_DRSSETTINGS_CNTR0097W=CNTR0097W: Memory-to-memory replication settings for EJB container is missing.
Message.Explanation: Stateful session bean failover using memory-to-memory replication has been enabled, but the memory-to-memory replication settings are missing.
Message.UserResponse: Disable stateful session bean failover, or provide the settings for memory-to-memory replication for the EJB container.

Message.MsgText: ATTEMPT_TO_REFERENCE_MISSING_INTERFACE_CNTR0154E=CNTR0154E: Another component is attempting to reference the {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module. This bean does not support an implementation of the {2} interface, which the other component is attempting to reference.
Message.Explanation: The component that is attempting to reference this bean has a configuration error. The component has specified an unsupported interface for this bean.
Message.UserResponse: Change the ejb-ref tag or @EJB annotation on the component that is attempting to reference this bean so that it specifies a supported interface. Check the log file for a related exception, which indicates the calling component that has the configuration error.

Message.MsgText: SINGLETON_DEPENDS_ON_SELF_CNTR0201E=CNTR0201E: The {0} singleton session bean in the {1} module directly or indirectly depends on itself.
Message.Explanation: The bean was configured to depend on itself or another bean that indirectly depends on that bean through the @DependsOn annotation or the depends-on element in the ejb-jar.xml file.
Message.UserResponse: Remove or change the dependency on the specified bean, or change one of its dependencies to not depend on it.

Message.MsgText: NO_REMOTE_INTERFACE_CLASSES_CNTR9277I=CNTR9277I: The {0} Java archive (JAR) or Web archive (WAR) file does not contain remote interface classes for a level 3.0 enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: The specified JAR or WAR file does not contain any remote interface classes for a level 3.0 enterprise bean.
Message.UserResponse: If this module should contain remote interface classes for a level 3.0 enterprise bean, add these classes to the module.

Message.MsgText: SINGLETON_INVALID_CONCURRENCY_MANAGEMENT_CNTR0193E=CNTR0193E: The value, {0}, that is specified for the concurrency management type of the {1} enterprise bean class must be either Bean or Container.
Message.Explanation: The concurrency management type can be specified using either the @ConcurrencyManagement annotation or the concurrency-management-type tag in deployment descriptor for a Singleton session bean. The value must be either BEAN or CONTAINER for Singleton session beans.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the @ConcurrencyManagement annotation or the concurrency-management-type tag so that the value is either Bean or Ccontainer.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MIN_POOLSIZE_CNTR0057W=CNTR0057W: Minimum pool size specified for bean {0} not a valid integer: {1}. Default used instead.
Message.Explanation: Only a positive integer can be specified for the minimum pool size. The default value will be used.
Message.UserResponse: Change the value for the minimum pool size to a positive integer.

Message.Explanation: The container was unable to map exception to a valid CORBA exception.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: FBPK_READONLY_OVERRIDE_ALL_CNTR0061I=CNTR0061I: Read-only attribute on findByPrimaryKey method overridden to true for bean: <All>
Message.Explanation: The findByPrimaryKey read-only attribute has been specified to be overridden to true on all entity beans.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: JIT_VOID_CREATE_RETURN_CNTR5018E=CNTR5018E: The {2} method of the {1} interface, which has been configured as a home interface for the {0} bean, does not return the component interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, all create methods on a home interface must return the component interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the create methods on the home interface to return the component interface.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_EJBHOME_RETURN_CNTR5034E=CNTR5034E: The {2} method with the {3} return type on the {1} class for the {0} entity bean must return the {4} type. This type must be the same type as the corresponding home interface method.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the return type of the ejbHome methods for an entity bean class must match the corresponding home interface method.
Message.UserResponse: Change the return type of the method to the type that matches the corresponding home interface method.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SFSB_CALLBACK_METHOD_CNTR0242E=CNTR0242E: Because the {0} enterprise bean implements the javax.ejb.SessionBean interface, the {1} method must be a {2} method and not a {3} method.
Message.Explanation: For a stateful session bean, the Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification requires that the ejbRemove, ejbActivate, and ejbPassivate methods be treated as @PreDestroy, @PostActivate, and @PrePassivate life cycle callback interceptor methods, respectively. The ejbCreate method must be treated as an @Init method.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the deployment descriptor or annotation so that the method is the correct type of life cycle callback interceptor.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_REF_STANZA_CNTR0184W=CNTR0184W: The ibm-ejb-jar-bnd.xml file contained in the {0} module has more than one {1} stanza with name attribute of {2} for the {3} interceptor class. Only the last {1} stanza is used. The interceptor class is using the java:comp namespace for the {4} enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: An interceptor stanza contains more than one ejb-ref, resource-ref, resource-env-ref, or message-destination-ref stanza with the same value for its name attribute. Each ejb-ref, resource-ref, resource-env-ref, or message-destination-ref stanza is required to have a different name attribute value.
Message.UserResponse: Either remove the extranous stanza or change the value of its name attribute in one or more ejb-ref, resource-ref, resource-env-ref, or message-destination-ref stanza so that the name is unique within the interceptor stanza and within the session or message-driven stanza for the enterprise bean.

Message.MsgText: OUTPUT_FILE_ALREADY_EXISTS_CNTR9275E=CNTR9275E: The {0} output file already exists.
Message.Explanation: The specified output file must be a non-existing file.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a new output file name.

Message.MsgText: NO_ACTIVATION_SPEC_BINDING_CNTR0144E=CNTR0144E: The Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) binding with the {0} Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) name has a jca-adapter stanza that does not contain an activation-spec-binding-name value.
Message.Explanation: All bindings for message driven beans require a jca-adapter stanza containing an activation-spec-binding-name value.
Message.UserResponse: Check the binding file and ensure that all message-driven bindings include a jca-adapter stanza with an activation-spec-binding-name value.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_CONNECT_TO_ORB_CNTR0006W=CNTR0006W: EJBObject "{0}" could not be connected to the ORB.
Message.Explanation: The container failed to connect a deserialized stub (reference) object on an attempt to activate a stateful bean.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CONTAINER_TRANSACTION_XML_CNTR0121W=CNTR0121W: XML configuration error in ejb-jar.xml for jar: "{0}". The container-transaction element in error has trans-attribute element: "{1}".
Message.Explanation: All ejb-name elements within the container-transaction element must match valid ejb-name elements within the enterprise-beans element.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file so that all ejb-name elements within the container-transaction element match valid ejb-name entries in the enterprise-beans element.

Message.MsgText: NO_JCA_ADAPTER_BINDING_CNTR0143E=CNTR0143E: The Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) binding with the {0} Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) name does not contain a jca-adapter stanza.
Message.Explanation: All bindings for message driven beans require a jca-adapter stanza within the message-driven binding.
Message.UserResponse: Check the binding file and ensure that all message-driven bindings include a jca-adapter stanza.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_ROLES_SPECIFIED_IN_METHOD_ANNOTATION_CNTR0151E=CNTR0151E: The {0} role is specified multiple times in the @RolesAllowed annotation on the {1} method of the {2} enterprise bean class.
Message.Explanation: A specified role can be specified once in a @RolesAllowed annotation.
Message.UserResponse: Change the Java source code by removing the duplicate roles from this annotation. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9415E_NO_JNDINAME_SPECIFIED=CNTR9415E: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container properties for the {0} data source do not contain the property, name.
Message.Explanation: The properties that the embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container uses contain a data source with no Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) name specified.
Message.UserResponse: Add a name property for this data source to the properties file.

Message.MsgText: BEAN_HAS_NOT_BEEN_INSTALLED_CNTR0009W=CNTR0009W: An attempt to access bean "{0}" failed because it was not previously installed or problems occurred during its installation.
Message.Explanation: The Application Server made an attempt to access an enterprise bean that has not been installed in the container.
Message.UserResponse: Look for prior error messages that indicate that the bean installation has failed.

Message.MsgText: JIT_THROWS_CLAUSE_MISMATCH_CNTR5035W=CNTR5035W: Multiple interfaces of the {0} bean define the same method signature, but with different exceptions on the throws clause. The following signature will be used for determining the application exceptions for the method : {1}
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the exceptions defined on the throws clause of a method are used by the container to determine which exceptions are application exceptions. If the exceptions on the throws clause of a method vary by interface, then unexpected exception behavior will occur for some of the interfaces.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application so that all methods with the same signature define the same exceptions on the throws clause.

Message.MsgText: CONFLICTING_ANNOTATIONS_CONFIGURED_ON_CLASS_CNTR0152E=CNTR0152E: The class-level {0} and {1} annotations cannot be configured on the {2} enterprise bean class at the same time.
Message.Explanation: The annotations that are identified in this error message are in conflict with each other. Do not specify these annotations on the same class.
Message.UserResponse: Change the Java source code by removing one, or both, of the annotations from the specified class. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: PARTIAL_METHOD_INTERCEPTOR_ORDER_CNTR0228E=CNTR0228E: The {0} enterprise bean specifies method-level interceptors for the {1} method with the following interceptor-order list: {2}. This list is not a total ordering of the method-level interceptors for this bean. The list is missing the following interceptor names: {3}.
Message.Explanation: When the interceptor-order element is used, the specified ordering at the method-level must be a total order. The order must be over all of the interceptor classes that have been defined at that level and above. The only exception to this rule is when interceptor classes have been explicitly excluded by means of an exclude-class-interceptors or exclude-default-inteceptors element.
Message.UserResponse: Specify additional interceptor names on the method-level interceptor-order element for this bean. Then, the bean will provide a total ordering of the interceptors.

Message.MsgText: SINGLETON_XML_OVERRIDE_CONCURRENCY_MANAGEMENT_CNTR0194E=CNTR0194E: The value {0} that is specified in the ejb-jar.xml file for concurrency management type is not the same as the @ConcurrencyManagement annotation value {1} on the {2} enterprise bean class.
Message.Explanation: The deployment descriptor cannot override the value that is provided by the @ConcurrencyManagement annotation on a Singleton session bean.
Message.UserResponse: Remove or change the value in the ejb-jar.xml file so that it does not override the value in the @ConcurrencyManagement annotation.

Message.MsgText: EXISTING_FILE_PARAM_ERROR_CNTR9270E=CNTR9270E: The update file name parameter is not a Java archive (JAR), Web archive (WAR), or an enterprise archive (EAR) file type.
Message.Explanation: The update file name parameter must be a JAR, WAR, and EAR file type and include the file path.
Message.UserResponse: Invoke the createEJBStubs command with the -help option to view the command syntax.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_DURING_TRAN_RECOVERY_SETUP_CNTR0086E=CNTR0086E: Transaction recovery setup error occurred for resource adapter {0}, MDB {1}.
Message.Explanation: The createEndpoint method was called on the JCA MessageEndpointFactory object by the resource adapter, and the resource adapter passed an XAResource object as one of the parameters of createEndpoint method. However, the resource adapter life cycle manager encountered an error which prevented it from setting up transaction recovery for this resource adapter. The endpoint cannot be created successfully.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the log for a prior error message indicating the setup failure for the message-driven bean (MDB) that was bound to the resource adapter. Correct the error to eliminate this error message.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_REF_BINDING_CNTR0186E=CNTR0186E: The {0} bean in the {1} module of the {2} application has more than one {3} binding with the {4} name.
Message.Explanation: The ibm-ejb-jar.xmi or ibm-ejb-jar.xml file for the module has more than one binding for the same reference for the same EJB.
Message.UserResponse: Remove all but one of the bindings for the reference in the bean.

Message.MsgText: ML_DUPLICATES_DEFAULT_CNTR0222E=CNTR0222E: The {0} method-level interceptor for the {1} method of the {2} enterprise bean duplicates a name that is in the following default interceptor list: {3}
Message.Explanation: The interceptor class can be either a default interceptor or a method-level interceptor, but not both types.
Message.UserResponse: Eliminate the interceptor class from either the default interceptor list or the method-level interceptor list.

Message.MsgText: HOME_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0092W=CNTR0092W: Attempted to access EnterpriseBean {0}, that has not been started.
Message.Explanation: An application tried to access an enterprise bean of an application that has not been installed, has not been started, or did not start successfully.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the application has been installed and started. If the application has been installed and started, see the previous messages regarding the failure of the enterprise bean to start, and correct those problems.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_REMOVE_ANNOTATION_CNTR0233E=CNTR0233E: The {1} enterprise bean specifies an @Remove annotation on the {0} method. This annotation is not valid because this method is not a business method of this bean.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification requires that @Remove annotations be applied to business methods of a stateful session bean.
Message.UserResponse: Either relocate the @Remove annotation to a business method of this bean, or change the specified method to be a business method.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_FINAL_METHOD_CNTR5106E=CNTR5106E: The {0} method on the {1} class must not be declared as final for the {2} bean.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, all methods of the bean class and any superclass must not be declared as final when the bean class is exposed as a no-interface view. And, business methods must not be declared as final.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application so the method is not declared as final.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_READ_FILE_CNTR9251E=CNTR9251E: Unable to read from the {0} file.
Message.Explanation: The specified file could not be opened for read operation.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the file system permissions setting for this file.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_THROW_REMOTE_CNTR5101W=CNTR5101W: The {0} method on the {1} interface should not define the java.rmi.RemoteException exception on the throws clause.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the throws clause of remote business interface methods should not include the java.rmi.RemoteException exception.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the RemoteException exception from the throws clause of the method. Also, you can change the interface to implement the java.rmi.Remote interface or change the application to not use the interface as an EJB remote interface.

Message.MsgText: JIT_NO_EJBFIND_METHOD_CNTR5030E=CNTR5030E: The {2} method of the {1} home interface for the {0} entity bean does not define a corresponding ejbFind method on the {3} class.
Message.Explanation: The method of the home interface for the entity bean does not define a corresponding ejbFind method on the class.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bean class to provide an ejbFind method that corresponds to the method.

Message.MsgText: JIT_MISSING_LOCAL_HOME_CNTR5002E=CNTR5002E: The {0} bean is configured with the {1} local component interface, but a local home interface has not been provided.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, a local home interface must be provided when a local component interface is provided.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application configuration to provide a local home interface for the bean.

Message.MsgText: NO_BEANS_IN_MODULE_CNTR9269W=CNTR9269W: The {0} Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) module does not have any enterprise beans configured.
Message.Explanation: EJB modules must contain one or more enterprise beans.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that one or more enterprise beans are configured for this module. The enterprise beans must use either an ejb-jar.xml file , or source code annotations.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9403E_DUPLICATE_MODULE_BASENAME=CNTR9403E: The embeddable enterprise bean container cannot start multiple modules with the same file name: {0} and {1}
Message.Explanation: User code has directed the embeddable container to start multiple modules with the same file name.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a list of modules that does not have duplicate file names, or rename one of the modules with a unique file name.

Message.MsgText: NEGATIVE_STATEFUL_TIMEOUT_XML_CNTR0312E=CNTR0312E: The {0} Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) in the {1} module of the {2} application has a timeout value specified in the stateful-timeout deployment descriptor element which is negative: {3}.
Message.Explanation: The stateful timeout must be postive, or 0 to indicate no timeout, or -1 to indicate infinite timeout.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the stateful-timeout timeout element in the EJB deployment descriptor.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_STYLE_4_INTERCEPTOR_BINDING_CNTR0248E=CNTR0248E: More than one style 4 interceptor-binding element is provided in the deployment descriptor for the {0} method with the {1} signature of the {2} enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, only one style 4 interceptor-binding can be used for each method of a given method signature of an enterprise bean.
Message.UserResponse: Correct deployment descriptor so that only one style 4 interceptor-binding is used for the method of an enterprise bean.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_CLASS_INTERCEPTOR_CNTR0220E=CNTR0220E: CNTR0220E: The {0} interceptor class exists multiple times in the list of interceptors for the {1} enterprise bean. The following is the interceptor list for this bean: {2}
Message.Explanation: The @Interceptors annotation or the interceptor-class tag in the deployment descriptor was used to provide a list of interceptor class names. A class must exist only once in the interceptor class list.
Message.UserResponse: Eliminate the duplicate interceptor class from the interceptor class list. Or, change the interceptor class name, if an incorrect name was specified.

Message.MsgText: USER_LOGFILE_PROBLEM_CNTR9260E=CNTR9260E: The {0} exception occured while setting up the user log file.
Message.Explanation: The exception was not expected.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the file system permissions settings.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACTIVITY_SESSION_POLICY_CNTR0072E=CNTR0072E: Bean "{0}" attempted to use an invalid "Activate at" policy with a container managed Activity Session.
Message.Explanation: Beans that are configured to use an Activity Session that is container-managed must use an "Activate at" policy of "Activity Session" or must use a "Load at" policy of "Interval", "Daily", or "Weekly".
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that an "Activate at" policy of "Activity Session" or a "Load at" policy of "Interval", "Daily", or "Weekly" is used when using an Activity Session that is container-managed.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_RESENVREF_BINDING_CNTR0077W=CNTR0077W: A reference to an ResourceEnvRef could not be found in the deployment descriptor for the WebApp or EnterpriseBean with the display name {0}.
Message.Explanation: The Java Enterprise Edition (Java EE) component might have specified binding information that is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the binding information in the deployment descriptor for the Java EE component is correct.

Message.MsgText: IMPROPER_REMOTE_JNDI_BINDING_PREFIX_CNTR0137E=CNTR0137E: The specific Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) binding name that is provided for a remote home or bean begins with ejblocal:. The {2} remote binding name that is specified for the home or {0} bean in the {1} module cannot begin with ejblocal:.
Message.Explanation: The remote binding name for the given bean or home cannot begin with ejblocal:.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the remote binding name for the bean or home in the specified module.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9408W_STOP_MODULE_FAILURE=CNTR9408W: The Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) module, {0} failed to stop. Exception: {1}
Message.Explanation: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container failed to shutdown the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) module due to the exception. The enterprise beans might still be bound into JNDI and are still accessible to clients. Future attempts to re-start that module might fail due to naming or other resource collisions.
Message.UserResponse: Resolve the failure by examining the exception, the logs, and the FFDC output. If other modules stop cleanly, examine the failing module.

Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_COMMIT_CONNECTION_CNTR0027W=CNTR0027W: Failed to commit connection: {0}
Message.Explanation: An SQLException occurred when trying to commit a Datasource connection.
Message.UserResponse: See the vendor-specific documentation for the database product you are using. Typically a vendor-specific exception code will be displayed as part of the SQLException. This exception code can be used, in combination with the vendor-specific documentation, to determine the cause of the exception.

Message.MsgText: METHOD_NAME_INVALID_FOR_DEFAULT_CNTR0239E=CNTR0239E: The method-name element is not valid for a style 1 interceptor-binding element.
Message.Explanation: The method-name element is not allowed in a style 1 interceptor-binding element.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the interceptor-binding to be a style 2 interceptor-binding element or remove the method-name element.

Message.MsgText: POOLSIZE_VALUES_CNTR0060I=CNTR0060I: (Min,Max) pool size is ({0},{1}) for bean {2}
Message.Explanation: These are the minimum pool size and maximum pool size values that will be used for this bean type.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACTIVITY_SESSION_POLICY_CNTR0070E=CNTR0070E: Bean "{0}" in an EJB 1.1 module attempted to use an invalid Local Transactions Boundary of "Activity Session".
Message.Explanation: Activity Sessions are not supported on EJB V1.1 modules.
Message.UserResponse: Select "Bean method" for Local Transactions Boundary.

Message.MsgText: CONFLICTING_RESOURCE_REFERENCE_CNTR0316E=CNTR0316E: A resource reference conflict was detected. {0}
Message.Explanation: A resource reference was defined in multiple places, with conflicting information.
Message.UserResponse: Change the resource reference definitions so they no longer conflict, or use a single resource reference and remove the duplicate resource reference definitions.

Message.MsgText: OPTION_OVERSPECIFIED_CNTR9252E=CNTR9252E: The {0} option was specified multiple times.
Message.Explanation: An option may only be specified once per createEJBStubs command invocation.
Message.UserResponse: Invoke the createEJBStubs command with -help option to view the command syntax.

Message.MsgText: NUMBER_FORMAT_EXCEPTION_CNTR0010W=CNTR0010W: NumberFormatException occurred while converting <env-entry-name> {0} <env-entry-value> {1}: {2}
Message.Explanation: The container was unable to process an environment entry due to a NumberFormatException.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the value for the environment entry is a valid string representation for the specified type.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_DRSEVENT_REPLICATION_UP_CNTR0113I=CNTR0113I: SfDRSControllerInstance {0} received event REPLICATION_UP.
Message.Explanation: The SfDRSControllerInstance that is specified received the event REPLICATION_UP.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_ENTRYKEY_CNTR0102E=CNTR0102E: Method {0} entryKey is null.
Message.Explanation: The specified method was passed a entryKey parameter that is null.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_DRSEVENT_REPLICATION_DOWN_CNTR0114I=CNTR0114I: SfDRSControllerInstance {0} received event REPLICATION_DOWN.
Message.Explanation: The SfDRSControllerInstance that is specified received the event REPLICATION_DOWN.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_SUBCLASS_REMOTE_EX_CNTR5102E=CNTR5102E: The {0} application exception that is defined on the {1} method of the {2} interface must not be defined as a subclass of the java.rmi.RemoteException exception.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, an application exception must not be defined as a subclass of the java.rmi.RemoteException exception.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application so that there are no remote business interface methods that are defined with a java.rmi.RemoteException subclass on the throws clause.

Message.MsgText: STARTUP_SINGLETON_SESSION_BEAN_INITIALIZATION_FAILED_CNTR0190E=CNTR0190E: The {0} startup singleton session bean in the {1} module failed initialization with exception: {2}
Message.Explanation: Startup Singleton Session bean instances are created as part of application start processing. Any failure will result in the application failing to start.
Message.UserResponse: Eliminate cause of the exception that is attached to this error message.

Message.MsgText: RA_DOES_NOT_SUPPORT_XATRANSACTIONS_CNTR0087E=CNTR0087E: Resource adapter {0} is not allowed to pass a non null XAResource to createEndpoint method for MDB {1}.
Message.Explanation: The createEndpoint method was called on the JCA MessageEndpointFactory object by the resource adapter, and the resource adapter passed an XAResource object to the createEndpoint method. Transaction recovery for this resource adapter is not supported, because the resource adapter indicated that it does not support XA transactions. The resource adapter is not allowed to pass an XAResource object to the createEndpoint method.
Message.UserResponse: Have the Resource Adaptor vendor correct the configuration or implementation of the resource adapter.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ASYNC_METHOD_INTF_VALID_SPECIFIED_CNTR0205E=CNTR0205E: The {0} bean in the ejb-jar.xml contains an async-method element with an invalid method-intf value. This value may only be "Local" or "Remote". "{1}" was specified.
Message.Explanation: The only valid values for the method-intf element of an asynchronous method are "Local" and "Remote". Any other value is invalid and the EJB Container will not recognize the containing async-method element.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the method-intf element's value to be either "Local" or "Remote".

Message.MsgText: LOCAL_TRAN_BOUNDARY_ACTIVITY_INVALID_CNTR0066E=CNTR0066E: Bean "{0}" attempted to use an invalid Local Transaction boundary value of "activity session".
Message.Explanation: The local transaction boundary of "activity session" is not valid for message-driven beans.
Message.UserResponse: Change the local transaction boundary from "activity session" to "bean method", and restart the application server.
