Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACTIVATION_POLICY_CNTR0043E=CNTR0043E: Bean "{0}" is attempting to use an invalid combination of ActivationPolicy and LoadPolicy on a work load managed server.
Message.Explanation: The user has specified 'Commit Option A' on an enterprise bean that is contained within a server that is work load managed. This configuration combination is not supported.
Message.UserResponse: Change the enterprise bean to use a different Commit Option, or change the server to not be work load managed.

Message.MsgText: UNEXPECTED_METHOD_CALL_CNTR0074E=CNTR0074E: Unexpected method call occurred in {0}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_CONVERT_REMOTE_2_STUB_CNTR0045W=CNTR0045W: Unable to convert remote object to stub. Possible reason="{0}".
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: CONFLICTING_TIMEOUT_METHOD_NAMES_CNTR0163E=CNTR0163E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has specified the {2} timeout method on a timeout-method tag in XML. Also, the bean has specified the {3} timeout method on an @Timeout annotation in the Java source code. This configuration conflicts.
Message.Explanation: Timer beans must configure only one timeout method.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the bean configuration to specify a single timeout method. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: THROWABLE_WHILE_CONSTRUCTING_JAVA_COMP_ENV_CNTR0055W=CNTR0055W: A Throwable exception was caught while attempting to construct <env-entry-name> {0} <env-entry-value> {1} {2}
Message.Explanation: The container caught a Throwable when the container was trying to create a java:comp/env entry.
Message.UserResponse: Take action based upon the exception message in message CNTR0055W.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_METHOD_PERMISSION_XML_CNTR0123W=CNTR0123W: XML configuration error in ejb-jar.xml for jar: "{0}". The method-permission element in error for EJB: "{1}".
Message.Explanation: All ejb-name elements within the method-permission element must match valid ejb-name elements within the enterprise-beans element.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file so that all ejb-name elements within the method-permission element match valid ejb-name entries in the enterprise-beans element.

Message.MsgText: BINDINGS_FILE_CONFIG_ERROR_CNTR0146E=CNTR0146E: The {0} bindings file contained in the {1} module has a configuration error at line number: {2}, column number: {3}.
Message.Explanation: The bindings file contains either a simple syntax error, or a semantic violation.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the log file for additional 'caused by' exceptions, which may provide specific parser message details. Correct the bindings file error and reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_INIT_CNTR0099I=CNTR0099I: {0} service has initialized successfully.
Message.Explanation: The z/OS Controller Service for Stateful SessionBean support in DRS has initialized successfully.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_WRITE_FILE_CNTR9254E=CNTR9254E: Unable to write to the {0} file.
Message.Explanation: The specified file could not be opened for write operation.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the file system permissions setting for this file.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_NULLTOKEN_CNTR0101E=CNTR0101E: Method {0} token is null.
Message.Explanation: The specified method was passed a servant token that is null.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: INCOMPLETE_EXCEPTION_LIST_CNTR0034I=CNTR0034I: ContainerEJBException.getExceptionChain is returning an incomplete list of exceptions.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: PERSISTENCE_REF_DEPENDENCY_NOT_DECLARED_CNTR0315E=CNTR0315E: The {0} stateful session bean in the {1} module in the {2} application did not declare a dependency on the {3} persistence reference.
Message.Explanation: When a stateful session bean is located in a WAR, it must declare dependencies on all persistence context references and persistence unit references that it intends to access.
Message.UserResponse: Add the appropriate @PersistenceContext or @PersistenceUnit source code annotation to the stateful session bean, or add the appropriate persistence-context-ref or persistence-unit-ref element to the appropriate session element in the XML deployment descriptor.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_EXCEPTPROXY_CNTR0108E=CNTR0108E: Method {0} caught exception {1} while acquiring proxy for token = {2}.
Message.Explanation: The method that is specified caught an exception acquiring a proxy for processing the servant token.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_FILE_CNTR9274E=CNTR9274E: The createEJBStubs command cannot create the {0} file.
Message.Explanation: The specified file cannot be created on the file system.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the file system permissions settings for the specified directory.

Message.MsgText: ASYNC_METHOD_MUST_RETURN_VOID_OR_FUTURE_CNTR0206E=CNTR0206E: The {0} asynchronous method on the {1} bean has a return type of {2}. A return type of void or future<V> is required for asynchronous methods.
Message.Explanation: Asynchronous methods must return void or future<V>.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the asynchronous method implementation to return void or future<V>. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9407W_NO_MODULES=CNTR9407W: There are no valid Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) modules to start.
Message.Explanation: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container found no valid Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) modules to start. A valid EJB module contains a valid META-INF/ejb-jar.xml or classes with EJB annotations. This could be because no EJB module exists in the classpath, or that the javax.ejb.embeddable.modules property defined modules that do not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Review the classpath and the javax.ejb.embeddable.modules property to determine which EJB modules should be started.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ASYNC_METHOD_ELEMENT_SPECIFIED_PARMS_WITH_WILDCARD_METHOD_CNTR0204E=CNTR0204E: The ejb-jar.xml file declares a parameter on a wildcard asynchronous method element for the {0} session bean. Parameters may not be specified on wildcards.
Message.Explanation: The ejb-jar.xml file incorrectly specifies a method-params element inside an async-method element which contains a wildcard (*) method-name element. This is not allowed, per the EJB 3.1 specification.
Message.UserResponse: Either remove the method-params element from the XML or change the method-name element to represent a specific method with the specified method-params parameters.

Message.MsgText: CAUGHT_EXCEPTION_THROWING_NEW_EXCEPTION_CNTR0035E=CNTR0035E: EJB container caught {0} and is throwing {1}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: UNRECOGNIZED_PARAM_CNTR9256E=CNTR9256E: The {0} parameter is not recognized.
Message.Explanation: The parameter does not match any of the allowed input options.
Message.UserResponse: Invoke the createEJBStubs command with the -help option to view the command syntax.

Message.MsgText: SFSB_FAILOVER_NOT_ALLOWED_WITH_EXTEND_PERSIST_CNTX_CNTR0156E=CNTR0156E: The {0} stateful session bean in the {1} module is configured for failover. However, the session bean is also configured to use extended-scope persistence context. These configuration settings conflict.
Message.Explanation: Stateful sessions beans cannot be configured for both failover support and extended-scope persistence context support.
Message.UserResponse: Eliminate one of these two configuration settings for this bean. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: REQUIRED_BINDING_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0135E=CNTR0135E: The {0} message-driven bean (MDB) does not have a corresponding binding in the binding file.
Message.Explanation: A message-driven bean binding must exist in the binding file for each message driven bean.
Message.UserResponse: Check the ejb-jar-bnd.xml binding file for the MDB and ensure that a binding entry exists.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_SCHEDULE_VALUE_RANGE_CNTR0212E=CNTR0212E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has automatic timer metadata for the {2} method, but the {3} schedule field has a value that is out of range for that field.
Message.Explanation: The specified method has automatic timer metadata in the deployment descriptor or in a @Schedule or @Schedules annotation, but the specified field in the metadata has a value that is out of bounds for that field.
Message.UserResponse: Change the field in the automatic timer metadata, or remove the automatic timer metadata.

Message.MsgText: NOT_EJB3_MODULE_CNTR9240I=CNTR9240I: The {0} Java archive (JAR) file is not an enterprise bean level 3.0 module.
Message.Explanation: The listed jar file is not configured as a level 3.0 module.
Message.UserResponse: If this module should have contained enterprise bean level 3.0 components, check the Java source code annotations, or ejb-jar.xml configuration data.

Message.MsgText: JIT_NO_POSTCREATE_METHOD_CNTR5028E=CNTR5028E: The {2} method of the {1} home interface for the {0} entity bean does not define a corresponding ejbPostCreate method on the {3} class.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the entity bean class must implement an ejbPostCreate method for every create method for a home interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bean class to provide an ejbPostCreate method that corresponds to the method.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ASYNC_METHOD_ELEMENT_MISSING_METHOD_NAME_CNTR0203E=CNTR0203E: The ejb-jar.xml declares an asynchronous method for the {0} session bean, but did not declare a method-name.
Message.Explanation: The specified session bean declares an asynchronous method in the ejb-jar.xml file, but did not specify the "method-name" element.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the ejb-jar.xml file and specify a method-name for the method that should be asynchronous (or "*" for all methods).

Message.MsgText: EJB_CONTEXT_DATA_NOT_AVAILABLE_CNTR0329E=CNTR0329E: The {0} type may only be injected into an enterprise bean instance or looked up within the context of an enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: When an enterprise bean context is not present, enterprise bean specific types, such as javax.ejb.EJBContext and javax.ejb.TimerService, are not available for injection or lookup.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application to only inject or lookup enterprise bean specific types within the context of an enterprise bean.

Message.MsgText: TO_MANY_PARAMS_CNTR9257E=CNTR9257E: Too many input parameters were specified.
Message.Explanation: The total number of allowed input parameters was exceeded.
Message.UserResponse: Invoke createEJBStubs command with the -help option to view the command syntax.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_STATEFUL_TIMEOUT_TIMEOUT_CNTR0313W=CNTR0313W: The system property {0} has a timeout value specified which is not a valid integer value: {1}. The default value of {2} minutes will be used instead.
Message.Explanation: Only a positive integer can be specified for the stateful timeout value. The default value will be used.
Message.UserResponse: Change the value for the stateful timeout to a positive integer.

Message.MsgText: CONNECTION_FACTORY_BINDING_NOT_SPECIFIED_CNTR0046E=CNTR0046E: Bean "{0}" did not specify a connection factory binding.
Message.Explanation: Neither the bean specific nor the default connection factory binding is specified for the bean.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a binding for the connection factory when installing the bean.

Message.MsgText: UNEXPECTED_EJB_START_FAILURE_CNTR0149E=CNTR0149E: The start up process for the {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module failed with the following exception: {2}
Message.Explanation: An error has occurred during the initialization and start process for the bean.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception message to determine why the bean did not start. Also, check the log for other exception messages that are related to starting this bean.

Message.MsgText: UNKNOWN_BINDINGS_FILE_CONFIG_ERROR_CNTR0147E=CNTR0147E: The {0} bindings file contained in the {1} module has a configuration error.
Message.Explanation: The bindings file contains either a simple syntax error, or a semantic violation.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the bindings file error and reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: STARTUP_SPECIFIED_ON_NON_SINGLETON_SESSION_BEAN_CNTR0189E=CNTR0189E: The {0} bean class can not be designated as a Startup bean using Java annotations or within the XML deployment descriptor.
Message.Explanation: Only Singleton Session beans can be defined with the Startup annotation or XML deployment descriptor.
Message.UserResponse: Eliminate the Startup Java annotation or XML deployment descriptor from this EJB class, or change the class to be a Singleton Session Bean.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_CREATING_CMP_PERSISTER_CNTR0032W=CNTR0032W: Error creating CMP persister using datasource: {0}
Message.Explanation: This message immediately follows the CNTR0031W message and provides the Datasource name that is used when starting the entity bean.
Message.UserResponse: Take the action described for the message CNTR0031W.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CONFIGURATION_CMP_RESOLVER_APPLICATION_CNTR0065E=CNTR0065E: CMP bean "{0}" attempted to use an unsupported Local Transaction resolution control value.
Message.Explanation: Only ContainerAtBoundary resolution control is supported for local transactions with container managed persistence (CMP) beans.
Message.UserResponse: Using an assembly tool, change "Resolution Control" to "ContainerAtBoundary" within the IBM Extensions tab for the CMP bean, and restart the server.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_JNDI_BINDING_COMBINATION_CNTR0130E=CNTR0130E: When a simple Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) binding name is specified for a bean or home, specific JNDI bindings cannot be specified. The {0} bean in The {1} module either must use a simple JNDI binding name or specific JNDI bindings, but not use both options.
Message.Explanation: Simple JNDI binding name cannot be mixed with specific JNDI bindings for a given bean or home.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the bindings file settings for the bean or home in the specified module.

Message.MsgText: CLASS_LOAD_ERROR_CNTR9262E=CNTR9262E: The {0} interface class could not be loaded. This can be caused by a spelling error, incorrect -cp option, failure to load parent class, or falure to load class on method parameter.
Message.Explanation: The specified class could not be loaded.
Message.UserResponse: Check for spelling errors, and make sure that all parent classes of this class are included in the input Java archive (JAR) file or enterprise archive (EAR) file, or are made available using the -cp option.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_XML_METHOD_PARAMS_CNTR0208E=CNTR0208E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has automatic timer metadata in the deployment descriptor for the {2} method, but the method parameter types are not valid for a timeout callback method.
Message.Explanation: An automatic timer can either have no parameters or a single javax.ejb.Timer parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Change the method parameter types, or remove the automatic timer metadata.

Message.MsgText: SESSION_SYNCH_METHOD_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0325E=CNTR0325E: The configured {0} session synchronization method {1} is not implemented by the {2} bean in the {3} module of the {4} application.
Message.Explanation: All configured session synchronization methods must be implemented by the bean.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bean implementation to include all configured session synchronization methods.

Message.MsgText: TIMERSERVICE_NP_NUM_THREADS_INVALID_CNTR0191E=CNTR0191E: The option to create a unique timer manager for non-persistent timers was chosen, but the number of timer threads has an unsupported value: {0}
Message.Explanation: When you share thread pools that are configured for persistent timers, you must configure multiple timer threads. On the EJBTimer configuration object, when the uniqueTimerManagerForNP attribute is set to true, the numNPTimerThreads attribute must be set to 1 or greater.
Message.UserResponse: In the EJB timer service settings of the application server, specify a positive value for the number of non-persistent timer threads. As an alternative, you can configure the timer service to use a scheduler for non-persistent timers by selecting the option to share thread pool configured for persistent timers (Specify false for the uniqueTimerManagerForNP attribute on the EJBTimer configuration object).

Message.MsgText: JIT_MUST_EXTEND_EJBHOME_CNTR5017E=CNTR5017E: The {1} interface, which has been configured as the remote home interface for the {0} bean, must extend the javax.ejb.EJBHome interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the configured remote home interface must extend the javax.ejb.EJBHome interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the interface to extend the javax.ejb.EJBHome interface or change the bean configuration to not specify the interface as the remote home interface.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_CREATION_FAILURE_CNTR0218E=CNTR0218E: An error occurred while creating persistent automatic timers for the {0} module: {1}
Message.Explanation: Either the module has metadata that is not valid, or the scheduler for the EJB timer service was unable to create the automatic timers.
Message.UserResponse: Check the module metadata and scheduler configuration.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_SCHEDULE_INCREMENT_INTERVAL_CNTR0214E=CNTR0214E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has automatic timer metadata for the {2} method, but the {3} schedule field has an interval value that is not valid.
Message.Explanation: The specified method has automatic timer metadata in the deployment descriptor or in a @Schedule or @Schedules annotation, but the specified field in the metadata has an interval value that is not valid. Increment values must be integers.
Message.UserResponse: Change the field in the automatic timer metadata, or remove the automatic timer metadata.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_EXCLUDE_CLASS_INTERCEPTORS_CNTR0224E=CNTR0224E: The {0} enterprise bean is missing a method-name tag on the exclude-class-interceptors element in the interceptor-binding element of the deployment descriptor.
Message.Explanation: The interceptor-binding element is using an exclude-class-interceptors element, which must specify a method-name tag.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the deployment descriptor by adding a method-name tag.

Message.MsgText: NO_MESSAGE_DESTINATION_BINDING_CNTR0145E=CNTR0145E: The Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) binding with the {0} Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) name has a jca-adapter stanza that does not contain a destination-binding-name value.
Message.Explanation: All bindings for message driven beans require a jca-adapter stanza containing a destination-binding-name value.
Message.UserResponse: Check the binding file and ensure that all message-driven bindings include a jca-adapter stanza with a destination-binding-name value.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9402E_INIT_ERROR=CNTR9402E: An error occurred while initializing the embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container {0}.
Message.Explanation: The process of scanning for Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) modules or initializing the embeddable EJB container failed and the container is no longer usable. Additional diagnostics might be found in FFDC output.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception type, and optionally, the FFDC output, to determine the cause of the initialization failure. A common reason for this error is an invalid EJB module is in the classpath.

Message.MsgText: TRANSACTION_COORDINATOR_NOT_AVAILABLE_CNTR0022E=CNTR0022E: Transaction coordinator not available. {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: SESSIONAL_CONCURRENT_TRANSACTION_ERROR_CNTR0064E=CNTR0064E: A bean instance of type "{0}" with an activity session based activation policy attempted to become involved with multiple concurrent transactions.
Message.Explanation: An enterprise Java bean (EJB) that is activated within an activity session should only participate in serial transactions. Having transaction attributes that vary, like REQUIRES for one method and REQUIRES_NEW or NOT_SUPPORTED for another, can cause this error.
Message.UserResponse: Review the transaction attributes that are assigned to the EJB methods, and verify that the sequence of the method calls do not result in multiple concurrent transactions for the same bean within an activity session.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_CREATION_CNTR0219I=CNTR0219I: The server created {0} persistent automatic timer or timers and {1} non-persistent automatic timer or timers for the {2} module.
Message.Explanation: The server has created the specified number of automatic timers for the specified module. If the server had previously created persistent automatic timers for this module, then no persistent automatic timers will be created on subsequent starts of the application.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_LIGHTWEIGHT_IMPL_CNTR0119E=CNTR0119E: The user-provided class "{0}" may not implement the com.ibm.websphere.ejbcontainer.LightweightLocal interface. Reason code = {1}.
Message.Explanation: Only enterprise Java bean (EJB) V2.x or later entity beans with a local interface may implement the com.ibm.websphere.ejbcontainer.LightweightLocal interface. The reason code identifies the specific violation as follows: 1 - The EJB is not an Entity bean. 2 - The bean is an EJB V1.x or container-managed persistence (CMP) V1.x entity bean. 3 - The EJB does not have a local interface defined.
Message.UserResponse: Change the EJB to be of the type "Entity", change the EJB deployment to version 2.0 or greater, change the EJB deployment to specify a local interface, or change the implementation to not implement the com.ibm.websphere.ejbcontainer.LightweightLocal interface.

Message.MsgText: DATASOURCE_NAME_NULL_CNTR0026W=CNTR0026W: DataSource name for CMP bean "{0}" is null. Bean will be unavailable for use.
Message.Explanation: No Datasource has been specified for the entity bean.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a Datasource for the entity bean, or specify a default Datasource for the module.

Message.MsgText: BEAN_INHERITANCE_ERROR_CNTR0159E=CNTR0159E: The {0} module has a configuration error in the inheritance relationship that is specified between the {1} parent bean and the {2} child bean.
Message.Explanation: There might be an error in the configuration extensions file for the module, or one of the two beans might not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the configured inheritance relationship in the extensions XML file for the module or supply the missing bean implementation.

Message.MsgText: FINDER_RESULT_EXCEEDED_LIMITS_CNTR0041W=CNTR0041W: Finder result collection exceeded limit. Only the first Integer.MAX_VALUE elements are processed.
Message.Explanation: The finder resulted in a collection that contains more than 2147483647 entity beans.
Message.UserResponse: Change the finder so that it does not result in a collection of entity beans that is more than 2147483647.

Message.MsgText: NON_COMPLIANT_WORK_MANAGER_CONFIG_CNTR0303W=CNTR0303W: The work manager configuration that is used for the EJB timer service does not comply with the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification.
Message.Explanation: The specification does not support any execution context information passed to the timeout method.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the work manager instance is configured to not pass context information, as required by the specification.

Message.MsgText: SINGLETON_DEPENDS_ON_NONEXISTENT_BEAN_CNTR0198E=CNTR0198E: The {0} singleton session bean in the {1} module depends on {2}, which does not exist.
Message.Explanation: The bean was configured to depend on another bean through the @DependsOn annotation or the depends-on element in the ejb-jar.xml file. However, the other bean does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Remove or change the dependency on the nonexistent bean.

Message.MsgText: BMAS_DEFINES_CMAS_ATTRIBUTES_CNTR0068W=CNTR0068W: Bean "{0}" or its home attempted to use an invalid combination of Bean Managed Activity Sessions and method-level Activity Session attributes.
Message.Explanation: An enterprise Java bean (EJB) or its home with "Bean Managed Transactions" should not declare "Container Managed Activity Session" attributes for its methods.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the "Container Managed Activity Session" attributes for the methods of this EJB or its home.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_POSTCREATE_RETURN_CNTR5029E=CNTR5029E: The {2} method with the {3} return type on the {1} class for the {0} entity bean must return void.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the return type of all ejbPostCreate methods for an entity bean class must be void.
Message.UserResponse: Change the return type of the method to void.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9405I_START_MODULE=CNTR9405I: The Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) module, {0}, is starting.
Message.Explanation: The embeddable EJB container is starting the identified Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) module. This includes binding the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) factories and homes to the JNDI and executing any EJB code that has been specified to run on startup.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: NON_COMPLIANT_WORK_MANAGER_CONFIG_CNTR0302W=CNTR0302W: The work manager configuration that is used for asynchronous methods does not comply with the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification.
Message.Explanation: The specification requires asynchronous methods to have security context information only.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the work manager instance is configured to pass security context only, as required by the specification.

Message.MsgText: JIT_WRONG_CREATE_RETURN_CNTR5020E=CNTR5020E: The {2} method of the {1} interface, which has been configured as a home interface for the {0} bean, does not return the {3} component interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, all create methods on a home interface must return the component interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the create methods on the home interface to return the component interface.

Message.MsgText: CL_DUPLICATES_DL_CNTR0240E=CNTR0240E: The {1} enterprise bean specifies the {0} class-level interceptor, which duplicates a name in the following default interceptors list: {2}
Message.Explanation: This interceptor class cannot be in both the default interceptor list and the class-level interceptor list unless the default interceptors are excluded at the class level.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the duplicate interceptor class from either the default or the class-level interceptor list. Or, exclude the default interceptors at the class level for this bean.

Message.MsgText: JIT_NO_EJBHOME_METHOD_CNTR5033E=CNTR5033E: The {2} method of the {1} home interface for the {0} entity bean does not define a corresponding ejbHome method on the {3} class.
Message.Explanation: TAccording to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the entity bean class must implement an ejbHome method for every home interface home method.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bean class to provide an ejbHome method that corresponds to the method.

Message.MsgText: LEGACY_STARTUP_BEAN_IN_WAR_CNTR0319E=CNTR0319E: The {0} bean is a startup bean, and is packaged inside of a Web archive (WAR) module, which is not allowed. Startup beans must be packaged inside of a stand-alone Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) module. Start-up behavior for an EJB component packaged inside of a WAR module is obtained by using a singleton session bean that is marked with the @Startup annotation, or the corresponding XML element.
Message.Explanation: A startup bean must not be packaged inside of a .war file.
Message.UserResponse: Package the startup bean inside a stand-alone EJB JAR module. Alternatively, use a singleton session bean marked with the @Startup annotation or the corresponding XML element, and package the bean in either an EJB JAR module or a WAR module.

Message.MsgText: STATEFUL_TIMEOUT_OVERFLOW_CNTR0309E=CNTR0309E: The {0} Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) in the {1} module of the {2} application contains a stateful timeout value {3} with time unit {4}. The conversion to milliseconds resulted in an overflow.
Message.Explanation: The stateful timeout is specified either via annotations or by deployment descriptor. The resulting conversion to milliseconds must be greater than zero and less than java.lang.Long.MAX_VALUE (9223372036854775807) to be valid.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the stateful timeout value for the Enterprise JavaBean identified by the message.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_CREATE_ROOT_DIRECTORY_FOR_STUBS_PROCESSING_CNTR9273E=CNTR9273E: The {0} directory could not be created.
Message.Explanation: The specified directory can not be created.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the file system permissions allow for directory creation.

Message.MsgText: INCOMPATIABLE_OPTION_WITH_CLASS_NAME_INPUT_CNTR9278E=CNTR9278E: The input type of a fully qualified class name is not compatible with the {0} option.
Message.Explanation: The input type of fully qualified class name is not compatible with the specified option.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the usage statement and either change the input type or remove the specified option.

Message.MsgText: EAR_LIBRARY_DIRECTORY_DISABLED_CNTR9276I=CNTR9276I: The {0} application has disabled the library directory. Java archive (JAR) and Web archive (WAR) files in the library directory will not be processed.
Message.Explanation: The application configuration data specified a library directory with a blank string for the library directory name. This action disables the library directory.
Message.UserResponse: If the library directory for this application should not be disabled, modify the application.xml configuration file in the application enterprise archive (EAR) file.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_SCHEDULE_UNINCREMENTABLE_CNTR0216E=CNTR0216E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has automatic timer metadata for the {2} method, but the {3} schedule field uses an increment.
Message.Explanation: The specified method has automatic timer metadata in the deployment descriptor or in a @Schedule or @Schedules annotation, but the specified field in the metadata uses an increment. You can use increments for the second, minute, and hour fields only.
Message.UserResponse: Change the field in the automatic timer metadata, or remove the automatic timer metadata.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ACTIVITY_SESSION_POLICY_CNTR0069E=CNTR0069E: Bean "{0}" in an EJB 1.1 module attempted to use an invalid "Activate at" policy of "Activity Session".
Message.Explanation: Activity Sessions are not supported for EJB V1.1 modules.
Message.UserResponse: Select "Once" or "Transaction" for the "Activate At" policy.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_KEYVALUE_CNTR0103E=CNTR0103E: Method {0} value is null.
Message.Explanation: The specified method was passed a entryKey value that is null.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: NO_MESSAGE_LISTENER_INTERFACE_CNTR0126E=CNTR0126E: The {0} message-driven bean (MDB) class does not define a message listener interface.
Message.Explanation: A message-driven bean must define a message listener interface using XML, annotations, or the implements clause of the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) class.
Message.UserResponse: Check the XML and Java source for the MDB class and specify the message listener interface.

Message.MsgText: ENGLISH_ONLY_INFO_MESSAGE_CNTR8990I=CNTR8990I: This message is an English-only Informational message: {0}.
Message.Explanation: This informational message is not translated.
Message.UserResponse: See message for details.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CACHE_RELOAD_POLICY_CNTR0094E=CNTR0094E: Entity bean "{0}" has been configured with a BeanCache LoadPolicy that will reload the Entity at an interval, but the Entity bean is not configured for EJB 2.x container managed persistence".
Message.Explanation: A Bean Cache LoadPolicy that reloads an entity bean at intervals is only supported for EJB V2.x container-managed persistence (CMP) beans.
Message.UserResponse: Change the Bean Cache LoadPolicy to a value that is supported by the bean type, or change the bean to use EJB V2.x container-managed persistence.

Message.MsgText: AMBIGUOUS_REFERENCE_TO_DUPLICATE_INTERFACE_CNTR0155E=CNTR0155E: Another component is attempting to reference the {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module. This bean supports both local and remote implementations of the {2} interface, which the other component is attempting to reference.
Message.Explanation: The component that is attempting to reference the bean has a configuration error. The component has not specified whether to invoke the local or remote interface on this bean.
Message.UserResponse: Change the ejb-ref tag or @EJB annotation on the component that is attempting to reference this bean so that it specifies either the local or the remote interface of the bean. Check the log file for a related exception, which indicates the calling component that has the configuration error.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_EXCLUDE_LIST_XML_CNTR0124W=CNTR0124W: XML configuration error in ejb-jar.xml for jar: "{0}". The exclude-list element in error for EJB: "{1}".
Message.Explanation: All ejb-name elements within the exclude-list element must match valid ejb-name elements within the enterprise-beans element.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file so that all ejb-name elements within the exclude-list element match valid ejb-name entries in the enterprise-beans element.

Message.MsgText: NO_COMPONENT_INTERFACE_CNTR9259E=CNTR9259E: No component interface specified for the {0} home.
Message.Explanation: Each configured home must have a component interface.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the configuration data for this home.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MAX_POOLTIMEOUT_CNTR0127W=CNTR0127W: The maximum pool size timeout specified for bean {0} is not a valid integer: {1}. The default value of {2} seconds is used instead.
Message.Explanation: Only a positive integer or zero can be specified for the maximum pool size timeout. The default value will be used.
Message.UserResponse: Change the value of the maximum pool size timeout to a positive integer or zero.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_METHOD_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0210E=CNTR0210E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has automatic timer metadata in the deployment descriptor for the {2} method, but no timeout callback method with that name was found.
Message.Explanation: The deployment descriptor contains automatic timer metadata for the specified method name, but no method with a timeout callback method signature was found by that name. A timeout callback method must have a void return type, and it must either have no parameters or have a single parameter with the type javax.ejb.Timer.
Message.UserResponse: Add a method with the specified name, change the method signature of an existing method with that name, or remove the timer from the deployment descriptor.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_SUBCLASS_RUNTIME_EX_CNTR5103E=CNTR5103E: The {0} application exception that is defined on the {1} method of the {2} interface must not be defined as a subclass of the java.lang.RuntimeException exception.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, an application exception for a component interface must not be defined as a subclass of the java.lang.RuntimeException exception.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application so that remote component interface methods are not defined with a java.lang.RuntimeException subclass on the throws clause.

Message.MsgText: WS_EJBPROXY_FAILURE_CNTR0177E=CNTR0177E: Failure occurred attempting to create a Web service endpoint proxy for the {0} bean in the {1} module of the {2} application : {3}
Message.Explanation: A session bean is not allowed to implement both a Web service Provider interface and a JAX-RPC Web service endpoint interface.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the configured JAX-RPC Web service endpoint interface from the ejb-jar.xml file, or change the bean implementation so that it does not implement the Web service Provider interface.

Message.MsgText: NON_APPLICATION_EXCEPTION_METHOD_ON_BEAN_CNTR0020E=CNTR0020E: EJB threw an unexpected (non-declared) exception during invocation of method "{1}" on bean "{2}". Exception data: {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception, which is not declared on the EJB method signature, was created when the EJB container attempted to invoke this EJB method.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the origin of the exception. If the exception originates from customer-written code, correct the cause of the exception. If not, visit the IBM support Web site for information on problem determination.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_TO_CLOSE_CONNECTION_CNTR0028W=CNTR0028W: Failed to close connection: {0}
Message.Explanation: An SQLException occurred when trying to close a Datasource connection.
Message.UserResponse: See the vendor-specific documentation for the database product you are using. Typically a vendor-specific exception code will be displayed as part of the SQLException. This exception code can be used, in combination with the vendor-specific documentation, to determine the cause of the exception.

Message.MsgText: NAME_ALREADY_BOUND_FOR_EJB_CNTR0172E=CNTR0172E: The {0} interface of the {1} bean in the {2} module of the {3} application cannot be bound to the {4} name location. The {5} interface of the {6} bean in the {7} module of the {8} application has already been bound to the {4} name location.
Message.Explanation: Each enterprise bean interface must specify a unique binding location.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the binding file for one of these two bean interfaces so that each interface has a unique binding location.

Message.MsgText: INCOMPLETE_EJB_BINDING_CNTR0142W=CNTR0142W: The Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) binding with the {0} Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) name does not contain an enterprise bean stanza.
Message.Explanation: All EJB bindings require an enterpriseBean stanza within the ibm-ejb-jar-bnd.xml file.
Message.UserResponse: Check the ibm-ejb-jar-bnd.xml file and ensure that all EJB bindings include an enterprise bean stanza.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9414E_CONFIG_READ_FAIL=CNTR9414E: Failed to bind data source into JNDI using the name, {0}. Exception: {1}
Message.Explanation: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container was unable to bind a javax.sql.DataSource instance into the JNDI namespace.
Message.UserResponse: Resolve the failure by examining the exception, the logs, and the FFDC output.

Message.MsgText: NP_TIMER_RETRY_LIMIT_REACHED_CNTR0179W=CNTR0179W: Non-persistent timer maximum number of retries {0} was reached.
Message.Explanation: The maximum number of retries configured on the EJB timer service (nonPersistentTimerRetryCount on the EJBTimer configuration object) has been reached. No further retries will be attempted until a timout method succeeds.
Message.UserResponse: Determine the cause of the failing timeout method, or increase the maximum number of retries.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_METHOD_AMBIGUOUS_CNTR0314E=CNTR0314E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has timer metadata in the deployment descriptor that targets the {2} method, but does not indicate whether the targeted method accepts zero or one parameters. Both a zero parameter and a one parameter version of the {2} method were found in the class hierarchy of the bean.
Message.Explanation: The deployment descriptor defines a timer that targets the specified method, but does not indicate how many parameters that method accepts. Multiple methods have that same name in the class hierarchy of the bean, which are eligible to receive timer callbacks. As a result, the EJB container is unable to determine which method the timer must target.
Message.UserResponse: Change the deployment descriptor so that the timer explicitly indicates whether it targets the zero parameter or the one parameter version of the method.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_SCHEDULE_LIST_VALUE_CNTR0215E=CNTR0215E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has automatic timer metadata for the {2} method, but the {3} schedule field has a list value that is not valid.
Message.Explanation: The specified method has automatic timer metadata in the deployment descriptor or in a @Schedule or @Schedules annotation, but the specified field in the metadata has a value for a list that is not valid. List values must be integers, keywords, or ranges.
Message.UserResponse: Change the field in the automatic timer metadata, or remove the automatic timer metadata.

Message.MsgText: POTENTIAL_LOST_UPDATE_CNTR0038W=CNTR0038W: The TX attribute needs to be changed to eliminate potential lost updates to bean {0} when used concurrently by multiple transactions. The bean should not be using the TX_NOT_SUPPORTED, TX_NEVER, or TX_SUPPORTS transaction attribute.
Message.Explanation: A transaction was started with the TX_NOT_SUPPORTED, TX_NEVER, or the TX_SUPPORTS transaction attribute. The transaction updated a container managed persistence (CMP) entity bean, and the transaction is storing the update to the persistent store. If a concurrent transaction uses the CMP entity bean with the same primary key value, the updates of one transaction might overlay the updates of the other transaction.
Message.UserResponse: The application must ensure that concurrent transactions never update a CMP entity bean with the same primary key value. If that cannot be done, then whichever bean begins the transaction must use a transaction attribute other than TX_NEVER, TX_NOT_SUPPORTED, or TX_SUPPORTS to ensure that data consistency is maintained.

Message.MsgText: ORPHAN_BINDING_ENTRY_CNTR0169E=CNTR0169E: The {0} enterprise bean, which is specified in the {1} binding within the {2} module, does not exist.
Message.Explanation: The enterprise bean name might be incorrect, or a binding might have been specified for a bean that does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the binding file. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MDB_TX_ATTR_CNTR0084E=CNTR0084E: Method {0} of MDB {1} is deployed with an incorrect transaction attribute.
Message.Explanation: A method of a message-driven bean (MDB) is required to be deployed with a transaction attribute of "requires", "not supported", or "bean managed".
Message.UserResponse: Redeploy the application using "requires", "not supported", or "bean managed" as the transaction attribute for the method of the MDB.

Message.MsgText: MDB_ACTIVATION_SPEC_INFO_CNTR0180I=CNTR0180I: The {0} message-driven bean in the {1} module of the {2} application is bound to the {3} activation specification.
Message.Explanation: When the message-driven bean starts, the specified activation specification will be used to activate the message endpoint.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_CUSTOM_EJBFIND_RETURN_CNTR5032E=CNTR5032E: The {2} method with the {3} return type on the {1} class for the {0} entity bean must return the {4} primary key class, the java.util.Collection class, or the java.util.Enumeration class.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the return type of all custom ejbFind methods for an entity bean class must be the primary key class, the java.util.Collection class, or the java.util.Enumeration class.
Message.UserResponse: Change the return type of the method to the primary key class, the java.util.Collection class, or the java.util.Enumeration class.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_CLASSPATH_PARAM_CNTR9264E=CNTR9264E: The required class path name parameter was not specified.
Message.Explanation: For the -cp option, the class path name must be provided as the next parameter.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the usage statement and provide the required class path name parameter.

Message.MsgText: JAX_RPC_ENDPOINT_IN_WAR_CNTR0317E=CNTR0317E: The {0} bean is packaged inside a WAR module and has been defined as a JAX-RPC endpoint using the ejb-jar.xml descriptor. The {1} interface is declared as the JAX-RPC endpoint. However, beans packaged in a WAR module are not supported as JAX-RPC endpoints. Package the bean in an EJBJAR module, or remove the service endpoint interface from the deployment descriptor.
Message.Explanation: An Enterprise JavaBean may not be declared as a JAX-RPC endpoint and packaged inside a WAR module.
Message.UserResponse: Package the Enterprise JavaBean in an EJBJAR module. Or, update to ejb-jar.xml descriptor to no longer declare the Enterprise JavaBean as a JAX-RPC endpoint.

Message.MsgText: CONFLICTING_ANNOTATIONS_CONFIGURED_ON_METHOD_CNTR0150E=CNTR0150E: The {0} annotation and the {1} annotation cannot both be configured on the {2} method of the {3} enterprise bean class.
Message.Explanation: The annotations that are identified in this error message are in conflict with each other. Do not specify these annotations on the same method.
Message.UserResponse: Change the Java source code by removing one or both of the annotations from the specified method. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: COLLABORATOR_THREW_UNEXPECTED_EXCEPTION_CNTR0012W=CNTR0012W: Collaborator {0} threw unexpected exception - proceeding with remaining collaborators. Exception data:{1}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MDB_CALLBACK_METHOD_CNTR0243E=CNTR0243E: Because the {0} enterprise bean implements the javax.ejb.MessageDriven interface, the {1} method must be a {2} method and not a {3} method.
Message.Explanation: For a message driven bean, the Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification requires that the ejbCreate and ejbPassivate methods be treated as @PostConstruct and @PreDestroy life cycle callback interceptor methods, respectively.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the deployment descriptor or annotation so that the method is the correct type of life cycle callback interceptor.

Message.MsgText: POOLSIZE_MISSING_EQUALS_SIGN_CNTR0062W=CNTR0062W: An equals sign was not found in the pool size specification string {0}
Message.Explanation: The format of a pool size specification is: bean_name=min,max . An equals sign must be present between the bean name and the minimum value and the maximum value.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that an equals sign is present between the bean name and the minimum value and the maximum value.

Message.MsgText: BAD_LOG_FLIE_CNTR9253E=CNTR9253E: The {0} log file name parameter is not correct.
Message.Explanation: The log file name must point to a file, including the directory path. Also, the log file name may not begin with "-".
Message.UserResponse: Invoke the createEJBStubs command with the -help option to view the command syntax.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_EXCLUDE_DEFAULT_INTERCEPTORS_CNTR0225E=CNTR0225E: The exclude-default-interceptors element in the deployment descriptor is not valid for a style 1 interceptor-binding element.
Message.Explanation: The interceptor-binding element is using an exclude-default-interceptors element which is only valid for a style 2, style 3, or style 4 interceptor-binding element.
Message.UserResponse: Eliminate the exclude-default-intercrptor element. Or, change the ejb-name tag within the interceptor-binding element to provide a specific enterprise bean name.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_PASSIVATE_STATEFUL_BEAN_CNTR0001W=CNTR0001W: A Stateful SessionBean could not be passivated: {0} {1} {2}
Message.Explanation: The container was not able to passivate a stateful session bean.
Message.UserResponse: Check that passivation directory exists, the process has write permissions in that directory, and that there is enough disk space.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_STYLE_1_INTERCEPTOR_BINDING_CNTR0245E=CNTR0245E: The {0} module of the {1} application has more than one style 1 interceptor-binding in the deployment descriptor. Only one style 1 interceptor-binding is allowed.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, only one style 1 interceptor-binding can be used for the module.
Message.UserResponse: Correct deployment descriptor so that only one style 1 interceptor-binding is used for the module.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_SCHEDULE_RANGE_BOUND_CNTR0213E=CNTR0213E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has automatic timer metadata for the {2} method, but the {3} schedule field has an range bound that is not valid.
Message.Explanation: The specified method has automatic timer metadata in the deployment descriptor or in a @Schedule or @Schedules annotation, but the specified field in the metadata has an range bound that is not valid. The upper and lower bound for a range must be non-negative integers or keyword values.
Message.UserResponse: Change the field in the automatic timer metadata, or remove the automatic timer metadata.

Message.MsgText: INJECTION_PROCESSING_FAILURE_CNTR0125E=CNTR0125E: Unable to process injection information for class: {0}.
Message.Explanation: The injection processors registered with the injection engine failed to identify and collect all the annotations associated with the class.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml and annotations on the class.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9420E_INVALID_CONNECTION_POOL_SPECIFIED=CNTR9420E: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container properties for the {0} data source contain a {1} ConnectionPool value that is not valid.
Message.Explanation: The properties that the embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container uses contain a data source with a ConnectionPool value that is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Change the ConnectionPool property value for this data source to a valid value. Valid values are names of a connection pool.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_INTERCEPTOR_METHOD_CNTR0223E=CNTR0223E: Only one method in the {0} class is allowed to be a {1} interceptor method.
Message.Explanation: More than one method of this class is specified as an interceptor method of the given type. The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification does not allow you to have multiple interceptor methods of the same type for this class.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the Java source code annotations or deployment descriptor for this class so that it only contains a single interceptor method of the given type.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9400I_SCANNING_MODULES=CNTR9400I: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container is scanning for Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) modules to start.
Message.Explanation: The embeddable container is scanning the classpath for valid Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) modules. Valid EJB modules contain an ejb-jar.xml file or Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) annotations.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_LIFECYCLE_SIGNATURE_CNTR0232E=CNTR0232E: The {0} method does not have the required method signature for a {1} method of a interceptor class.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification requires that life cycle methods of an interceptor class have the following signature, without a throws clause: void <METHOD> (InvocationContext)
Message.UserResponse: Correct the method signature for this interceptor.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_APPLICATION_DRSSETTINGS_CNTR0096W=CNTR0096W: Application configuration for session bean "{0}" is missing override of memory-to-memory replication settings.
Message.Explanation: The session bean is configured to override the memory-to-memory replication settings at the application level, but no settings for memory-to-memory replication are provided at the application level.
Message.UserResponse: Disable the override at the application level, or provide the settings for memory-to-memory replication for this session bean.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_AROUND_INVOKE_SIGNATURE_CNTR0230E=CNTR0230E: The {0} method does not have the required method signature for a {1} method.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification requires that around-invoke and around-timeout methods have the following signature: Object <METHOD>(InvocationContext) throws Exception
Message.UserResponse: Correct the method signature of this interceptor.

Message.MsgText: EJBSTORE_DISABLED_CNTR0117I=CNTR0117I: Container-managed ejbStore() call will be bypassed on bean: "{0}" if it has not been modified in the current transaction.
Message.Explanation: The bean has been configured to prevent the enterprise Java bean (EJB) container from invoking the ejbStore() method if the bean has not been modified. This behavior is not compliant with the EJB V2.0 or later specifications, but it can improve performance.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: JIT_NO_INIT_METHOD_CNTR5025E=CNTR5025E: The {2} method of the {1} home interface for the {0} bean does not define a corresponding init or ejbCreate method on the {3} class.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the bean class must implement an ejbCreate or init method for every create method for a home interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bean class to provide an ejbCreate or init method that corresponds to the method.

Message.MsgText: SINGLETON_INVALID_ACCESS_TIMEOUT_CNTR0192E=CNTR0192E: The access timeout value {0} is not valid for the enterprise bean {1} method of the {2} class. The value must be -1 or greater and less than java.lang.Long.MAX_VALUE (9223372036854775807).
Message.Explanation: The access timeout is specified either via annotations or by deployment descriptor. The value must be -1 or greater and less than java.lang.Long.MAX_VALUE (9223372036854775807).
Message.UserResponse: Correct the access timeout value for the method identified by the message. A method name of "*" is used in deployment descriptor to indicate all methods of the singleton class. If annotation is used and @AccessTimeout annotation is not found on the method, correct the @AccessTimeout annotation at class level.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_LIFECYCLE_SIGNATURE_CNTR0231E=CNTR0231E: The {0} method signature is not valid as a {1} method of an enterprise bean class.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification requires that life cycle methods of an enterprise bean have the following signature, without a throws clause: void <METHOD>()
Message.UserResponse: Correct the method signature for this interceptor.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_STARTING_CMP_BEAN_CNTR0031W=CNTR0031W: Error starting CMP bean {0}: {1}
Message.Explanation: An entity bean might have been bound to a Datasource using a Datasource name that is not valid or is not correct. If the Datasource name is correct, the Datasource might not be configured correctly.
Message.UserResponse: If the CNTR0026W message precedes this message, you need to provide the name of the Datasource. If CNTR0026W did not precede this message, check the datasource name that appears in the CNTR0032W message that follows this message. If a 'name not found' exception occurred, the Datasource name is most likely not correct. If the correct Datasource name is provided, then check the Datasource configuration. For example, you might have specified a database name, a user ID, or a password in the datasource configuration that is not correct.

Message.MsgText: INTERCEPTOR_CLASS_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0237E=CNTR0237E: The user-provided enterprise bean level 3.0 {0} interceptor class cannot be found or loaded.
Message.Explanation: An enterprise bean level 3.0 interceptor class cannot not be found or loaded.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the interceptor class is installed and configured correctly.

Message.MsgText: DEPENDS_ON_SPECIFIED_ON_NON_SINGLETON_BEAN_CNTR0197E=CNTR0197E: The {0} non-singleton enterprise bean has dependency metadata.
Message.Explanation: The bean was configured to depend on another bean through the @DependsOn annotation or the depends-on element in the ejb-jar.xml file. However, the bean is not a singleton session bean.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the dependency metadata, or change the type of the bean.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9401I_INIT=CNTR9401I: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container is initializing.
Message.Explanation: The embeddable container must initialize before the user code can access the enterprise beans.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: ENDPOINT_RECOVERY_ID_UNKNOWN_CNTR0082E=CNTR0082E: Cannot enlist XAResource since recovery ID for resource adapter {0} for MDB {1} is not known.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_KEYBYTES_CNTR0104E=CNTR0104E: Method {0} cannot convert entryKey to byte array.
Message.Explanation: The method that is specified was not able to convert the entryKey parameter to a byte array.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: ENGLISH_ONLY_WARN_MESSAGE_CNTR8991W=CNTR8991W: This message is an English-only Warning message: {0}.
Message.Explanation: This warning message is not translated.
Message.UserResponse: See message for details.

Message.MsgText: SIMPLE_BINDING_NAME_MISSUSED_CNTR0168W=CNTR0168W: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module within the {2} application is configured with a simple binding name, but has multiple local or remote interfaces. The naming locations that are used to bind these interfaces will differ from the simple binding name that is specified.
Message.Explanation: Because the enterprise bean has multiple interfaces, each binding name must be extended to make it unique.
Message.UserResponse: Complete one of the following actions: /n Look up the interfaces for this enterprise bean using the extended names. /n Change the configuration data for this bean to specify unique binding locations for each interface.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_RESREF_BINDING_CNTR0076W=CNTR0076W: A reference to an ResourceRef could not be found in the deployment descriptor for the WebApp or EnterpriseBean with the display name {0}.
Message.Explanation: The Java Enterprise Edition (Java EE) component might have specified binding information that is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Verify the binding information in the deployment descriptor for the Java EE component is correct.

Message.MsgText: TIMERSERVICE_WORKMANAGER_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0195E=CNTR0195E: The work manager associated with the {0} scheduler used by the EJB timer service could not be obtained.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to obtain the work manager.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the timer service scheduler has a work manager configured.

Message.MsgText: TIMER_BEAN_MUST_IMPLEMENT_EJBTIMEOUT_CNTR0160E=CNTR0160E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module is configured as timer bean. However, the bean does not implement the following required timeout method: ejbTimeout
Message.Explanation: Timer beans, which inherit from the TimedObject interface, must implement the following timeout method: ejbTimeout
Message.UserResponse: Correct the bean implementation to include the required method. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: JIT_NO_CREATE_METHOD_CNTR5019E=CNTR5019E: The {1} interface, which has been configured as a home interface for the {0} bean, does not define a create method.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, all home interfaces must define at least one create method.
Message.UserResponse: Change the home interface to define a create method.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_VALIDATION_FAILED_CNTR0301E=CNTR0301E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module of the {2} application has an automatic timer for the {3} method, but an incompatible change was made to the application since the server created the timer.
Message.Explanation: The server attempted to run a timeout callback method for an automatic timer, but an incompatible change was made to the application without removing the automatic timers.
Message.UserResponse: Stop the application and run the removeAutomaticEJBTimers command for the AdminTask object to manually clear the contents of the database. The server automatically recreates the timers when the application is restarted.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_DELETE_FILE_CNTR9267W=CNTR9267W: The createEJBStubs command could not delete the {0} file.
Message.Explanation: The specified file could not be deleted.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the file system permissions settings.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_STATEFUL_TIMEOUT_TIMEOUT_CNTR0307W=CNTR0307W: The {0} Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) in the {1} module of the {2} application has a timeout value specified in the StatefulTimeout annotation or stateful-timeout deployment descriptor element which is not a valid integer: {3}. The default value of {4} milliseconds will be used instead.
Message.Explanation: Only a positive integer can be specified for the stateful timeout value. The default value will be used.
Message.UserResponse: Change the value for the stateful timeout to a positive integer.

Message.MsgText: AMBIGUOUS_INIT_ANNOTATION_CNTR0235E=CNTR0235E: The name of the adapted create<METHOD> method must be specified for either the {0} method or the {1} method of the {2} enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: The @Init annotation is applied to multiple methods of the enterprise bean. The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification requires that the name of the adapted create<METHOD> method of the home or local home interface must be specified if there is any ambiguity.
Message.UserResponse: Use the value element of the @Init annotation to specify the name of the create<METHOD> on one of the two specified methods. This approach will remove the ambiguity.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9106E=CNTR9106E: Missing required server name.
Message.Explanation: A server name must be specified.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the usage statement, and specify a server name.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_SCHEDULE_VALUE_CNTR0211E=CNTR0211E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has automatic metadata for the {2} method, but the {3} schedule field has a value that is not valid.
Message.Explanation: The specified method has automatic timer metadata in the deployment descriptor or in a @Schedule or @Schedules annotation, but the specified field in the metadata has a value that is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Change the field in the automatic timer metadata, or remove the automatic timer metadata.

Message.MsgText: EJB_START_FAILED_CNTR0093E=CNTR0093E: Attempt to start EnterpriseBean {0} failed with exception: {1}
Message.Explanation: An error has occurred during the initialization and start of an EnterpriseBean.
Message.UserResponse: Take action based upon the exception message in message CNTR0093E.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9412E_JNDI_CLOSE_FAIL=CNTR9412E: An error occurred while shutting down the JNDI name space. Exception: {0}
Message.Explanation: The embeddable EJB container was unable to close the java:global namespace. This means that some Enterprise JavaBeans or other objects bound into the namespace could be leaked. Additionally, this could lead to JNDI problems if additional embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container instances are created.
Message.UserResponse: Resolve the failure by examining the exception, the logs, and the FFDC output.

Message.MsgText: STATEFUL_PERSISTENCE_CONTEXT_ACTIVATE_ONCE_CNTR0175W=CNTR0175W: The configured Activation Policy for the {0} bean in the {1} module of the {2} application has been changed from {3} to ONCE. A Stateful Session bean that references an extended persistence context must be configured with an Activation Policy of ONCE.
Message.Explanation: A Stateful Session bean that references an extended persistence context must be configured with an Activation Policy of ONCE.
Message.UserResponse: Change the Activation Policy configured for the bean to ONCE.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9105E=CNTR9105E: Missing required filter.
Message.Explanation: One of the three filters must be specified: -all -timer -app
Message.UserResponse: Examine the usage statement, and specify one of the three filters.

Message.MsgText: BEANCLASS_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0075E=CNTR0075E: The user-provided class "{0}" needed by the EnterpriseBean could not be found or loaded.
Message.Explanation: One or more of the implementation, home interface, remote interface, local interface, or other similar class for the bean could not be found or could not be loaded.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the implementation class, home interface, remote interface, and other classes for the bean are installed and configured correctly.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9104W=CNTR9104W: EJB timer service {0} not available on server {1} in node {2}.
Message.Explanation: The EJB timer service that is configured for the server that is specified is not available. The EJB timer service cannot start if there are no applications with TimedObject enterprise Java beans started on the server.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that an application with a TimedObject enterprise Java bean has been started on the server process that is specified.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_RENAME_FILE_CNTR9266E=CNTR9266E: The createEJBStubs command could not rename the {0} file to the {1} file.
Message.Explanation: The specified file could not be renamed.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the file system permissions settings. Also, make sure target file does not already exist.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_NOT_EXCEPTION_SUBCLASS_CNTR5107E=CNTR5107E: The {0} application exception defined on the {1} method of the {2} class must be defined as a subclass of the java.lang.Exception class.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, an application exception for an interface must be defined as a subclass of either the java.lang.Exception class or the java.lang.RuntimeException class.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application so that the exception is a subclass of either the java.lang.Exception class or the java.lang.RuntimeException class.

Message.MsgText: NEGATIVE_STATEFUL_TIMEOUT_ANN_CNTR0311E=CNTR0311E: The {0} Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) in the {1} module of the {2} application has a timeout value specified in the StatefulTimeout annotation which is negative: {3}.
Message.Explanation: The stateful timeout must be postive, or 0 to indicate no timeout, or -1 to indicate infinite timeout.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the StatefulTimeout annotation on the EJB.

Message.MsgText: BEAN_DOES_NOT_IMPLEMENT_REQUIRED_METHOD_CNTR0157E=CNTR0157E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module does not implement the {2} method. This method is part of the bean interface.
Message.Explanation: Enterprise beans must implement all of the methods that are specified on their interface classes.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the bean implementation to include all of the required methods. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_POOLSIZE_COMBO_CNTR0059W=CNTR0059W: Minimum pool size specified for bean {0} is greater than maximum pool size specified: ({1},{2}) Defaults used instead.
Message.Explanation: The maximum pool size must be greater than or equal to the minimum size. The default values will be used for the minimum pool size and the maximum pool size.
Message.UserResponse: Change the maximum pool size to be a value that is greater than or equal to the minimum pool size.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9103W=CNTR9103W: EJB timer {0} could not be found on server {1} in node {2}.
Message.Explanation: The EJB timer that is specified does not exist on the server that is specified. The EJB timer might have expired, or it might have been cancelled.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the identity of the EJB timer and the server name have been specified correctly. If the EJB timer does exist, the identity name is correct, and server name is correct, see any previous exceptions for more information.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_INTERCEPTOR_BINDING_CNTR0226E=CNTR0226E: The {2} enterprise bean specifies a style 4 interceptor-binding element for the {0} method with the {1} signature. A style 4 interceptor-binding cannot be used when a style 3 binding is also used for the same method of the same enterprise bean.
Message.Explanation: Style 3 and style 4 interceptor-binding elements cannot be specified on the same method of an enterprise bean.
Message.UserResponse: Eliminate either the style 3 or the style 4 interceptor-binding element for the specified method of this bean.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_CREATE_RETURN_CNTR5027E=CNTR5027E: The {2} method with the {3} return type on the {1} class for the {0} entity bean must return the {4} primary key class.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the return type of all ejbCreate methods for an entity bean class must be the primary key type.
Message.UserResponse: Change the return type of the method to the primary key class.

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_EVENTBYTES_CNTR0111E=CNTR0111E: Method {0} cannot convert event to byte array : stoken = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The method that is specified was not able to convert the event to a byte array.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: REASON_CODE_NOT_RECOGNIZED_CNTR0081E=CNTR0081E: setTranEnlistmentNotNeeded called with an unrecognized reason code of {0}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: CNTR9409W_STOP_FAILURE=CNTR9409W: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container failed to stop. Exception: {0}
Message.Explanation: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container failed to stop when the Close method was invoked due to the exception. Since this occurs after all the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) modules have been stopped, this is a problem with the embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container or its configuration.
Message.UserResponse: Resolve the failure by examining the exception, the logs, the FFDC output, and review the configuration of the embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_STYLE_2_INTERCEPTOR_BINDING_CNTR0246E=CNTR0246E: The {0} module of the {1} application has more than one style 2 interceptor-binding in the deployment descriptor. Only one style 2 interceptor-binding is allowed.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, only one style 2 interceptor-binding can be used for each enterprise bean.
Message.UserResponse: Correct deployment descriptor so that only one style 2 interceptor-binding is used for the enterprise bean.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_SLSB_CALLBACK_METHOD_CNTR0241E=CNTR0241E: Because the {0} enterprise bean implements the javax.ejb.SessionBean interface, the {1} method must be a {2} method and not a {3} method.
Message.Explanation: For a stateless session bean, the Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification requires that the ejbCreate, ejbRemove, ejbActivate, and ejbPassivate methods be treated as @PostConstruct, @PreDestroy, @PostActivate, and @PrePassivate life cycle callback interceptor methods, respectively.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the deployment descriptor or annotation so that the method is the correct type of life cycle callback interceptor.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_SCHEDULE_MISSING_DAY_OF_WEEK_CNTR0217E=CNTR0217E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has automatic timer metadata for the {2} method, but the {3} schedule field has an ordinal keyword without a day of the week.
Message.Explanation: The specified method has automatic timer metadata in the deployment descriptor or in a @Schedule or @Schedules annotation, but the specified field in the metadata has an ordinal keyword without a day of the week. The 1st, 2nd, 3rd, 4th, and 5th keywords must be followed by a keyword for the day of the week.
Message.UserResponse: Change the field in the automatic timer metadata, or remove the automatic timer metadata.

Message.MsgText: NON_APPLICATION_EXCEPTION_METHOD_CNTR0019E=CNTR0019E: EJB threw an unexpected (non-declared) exception during invocation of method "{1}". Exception data: {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception, which is not declared on the EJB method signature, was created when the EJB container attempted to invoke this EJB method.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the stack trace to determine the origin of the exception. If the exception originates from customer-written code, correct the cause of the exception. If not, visit the IBM support Web site for information on problem determination.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_BEAN_TYPE_FOR_ASYNCH_METHOD_CNTR0185E=CNTR0185E: The {0} bean in the {1} module of the {2} application has one or more asynchronous methods configured, but is not a session bean. Asynchronous methods can only be configured on session beans.
Message.Explanation: You can configure asynchronous methods on session beans only.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the asynchronous method from the bean.

Message.MsgText: FIRST_PARAM_ERROR_CNTR9250E=CNTR9250E: The first parameter must be a fully qualified class name, Java archive (JAR)file, Web archive (WAR)file, or enterprise archive (EAR) file.
Message.Explanation: The first parameter must be a fully qualified class name, a JAR file, a WAR file, or an EAR file. JAR, WAR, and EAR files must include the complete directory path.
Message.UserResponse: Invoke the createEJBStubs command with the -help option to view the command syntax.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_APPLICATION_EXCEPTION_FOR_VOID_ASYNCH_METHOD_CNTR0202E=CNTR0202E: The {0} asynchronous method on the {1} bean has a return type of void and has the {2} application exception(s) on its throws clause.
Message.Explanation: The method was configured to be asynchronous through the @Asynchronous annotation or the asynch-method element in the ejb-jar.xml file. Asynchronous methods with a void return type must not have application exceptions on the throws clause.
Message.UserResponse: Change the return type of method, remove the application exception from the throws clause, or change the metadata for the method so that it is not asynchronous.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9102E=CNTR9102E: Option {0} requires option {1}.
Message.Explanation: One of the options that is specified requires another option that has not been specified.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the usage statement, and specify the required option.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TX_ATTR_CNTR0089E=CNTR0089E: Transaction attribute {0} is not allowed for method "{1}" on EJB {2}.
Message.Explanation: The enterprise Java bean (EJB) Specification does not allow the transaction attribute that is configured for the EJB method. See the EJB Specification for further details.
Message.UserResponse: Change the deployment descriptor to specify a transaction attribute that is allowed for the EJB method.

Message.MsgText: IMPROPER_LOCAL_JNDI_BINDING_PREFIX_CNTR0136E=CNTR0136E: The specific Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) binding name provided for a local home or bean does not begin with ejblocal:. The {2} local binding name that is specified for the home or {0} bean in the {1} module does not begin with ejblocal:.
Message.Explanation: The local binding name for the specified bean or home does not begin with ejblocal:.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the local binding name for the bean or home in the specified module.

Message.MsgText: NO_SUCH_MDB_METHOD_CNTR0085E=CNTR0085E: MDB {0} must implement method {1} of interface {2}.
Message.Explanation: The resource adapter is calling a method that is not implemented by the message-driven bean (MDB).
Message.UserResponse: Determine if the MDB was deployed to use the correct resource adapter. If the bean is bound to the correct resource adapter, change the MDB to provide an implementation for the method.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INTERFACE_NOT_INTERFACE_CNTR5011E=CNTR5011E: The {1} class has been configured as a business or component interface for the {0} bean. However, the class is not an interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the configured business and component interfaces must be Java interfaces.
