Message.UserResponse: Change the bean configuration to provide Java interfaces.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9101E=CNTR9101E: Incompatible options: {0} {1}
Message.Explanation: Two of the options that are specified are not compatible and cannot be specified together.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the usage statement, and remove one of the specified options.

Message.MsgText: JNDI_BINDING_LOCATION_INFO_CNTR0167I=CNTR0167I: The server is binding the {0} interface of the {1} enterprise bean in the {2} module of the {3} application. The binding location is: {4}
Message.Explanation: The interface has been bound at the specified naming location.
Message.UserResponse: Use the specified naming location when attempting to look up this interface.

Message.MsgText: JIT_MISSING_CREATE_EX_CNTR5021E=CNTR5021E: The {2} method of the {1} interface, which has been configured as a home interface for the {0} bean, does not define the javax.ejb.CreateException exception on the throws clause.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the throws clause of all create methods on a home interface must contain the javax.ejb.CreateException exception.
Message.UserResponse: Change the create methods on the home interface to throw javax.ejb.CreateException.

Message.MsgText: COMMIT_OPTION_A_AND_OPTIMISTIC_CONCURRENCY_CONTROL_NOT_SUPPORTED_CNTR0049E=CNTR0049E: Bean is attempting to use an invalid combination of Commit Option A and Optimistic Concurrency.
Message.Explanation: The user has specified Commit Option A and Optimistic Concurrency Control on an enterprise bean. The Application Server does not support both Commit Option A and Optimistic Concurrency Control on an enterprise bean.
Message.UserResponse: Change the enterprise bean to use either Commit Option A or Optimistic Concurrency Control, but not both.

Message.MsgText: EXCEPTION_THROWN_BY_DISCARD_STRATEGY_CNTR0054W=CNTR0054W: Exception thrown by discard strategy {0} {1}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: CNTR9100E=CNTR9100E: Exception {0}
Message.Explanation: A general exception condition has been discovered.
Message.UserResponse: Combine this information with additional exception messages to perform additional problem determination.

Message.MsgText: TIMEOUT_ANNOTATION_OVERSPECIFIED_CNTR0161E=CNTR0161E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has specified the @Timeout annotation on more than one method.
Message.Explanation: Timer beans may only implement a single timeout method.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the bean implementation to include only one timeout method. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: POOLSIZE_VALUES_CNTR0128I=CNTR0128I: (Min,Max,Timeout) pool size is ({0},{1},{2}) for bean {3}.
Message.Explanation: These are the minimum pool size, maximum pool size, and maximum pool size timeout values that will be used for this bean type.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: WS_ENDPOINT_PROVIDER_CONFLICT_CNTR0176E=CNTR0176E: Web service Provider interface conflicts with the configured Web service endpoint interface {0} for the {1} bean in the {2} module of the {3} application.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: INVALID_LOAD_POLICY_CNTR0044W=CNTR0044W: Bean "{0}" is attempting to use an invalid combination of Activation Policy: Transaction and Load Policy : Activation. Defaulting Load Policy to : Transaction.
Message.Explanation: The activation policy specified for the enterprise bean is not supported. Option C, which is the default action taken, might not be the desired result. The combination of the Activation Policy and the Load Policy is the method in which the Application Server implements commit options A, B, and C in the Enterprise Java Bean (EJB) specification.
Message.UserResponse: Redeploy the enterprise bean using a combination of valid settings to eliminate this message.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TIMEDOBJECT_IMPL_CNTR0088E=CNTR0088E: The user-provided class "{0}" may not implement the javax.ejb.TimedObject interface.
Message.Explanation: Enterprise Java bean (EJB) V1.x, V2.0, and Stateful Session beans cannot implement the javax.ejb.TimedObject interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the EJB deployment to V2.1 or greater, change the implementation to not implement the javax.ejb.TimedObject interface, or change the EJB type.

Message.MsgText: STATEFUL_TIMEOUT_ON_NON_SFSB_CNTR0310W=CNTR0310W: The {0} Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) in the {1} module of the {2} application contains the stateful-timeout deployment descriptor element. stateful-timeout applies only to stateful session beans. The EJB container will ignore the stateful-timeout on this bean.
Message.Explanation: This element applies only to stateful session beans. The Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) container will ignore the stateful-timeout on this bean.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the stateful-timeout deployment descriptor element from the specified bean, or make the bean a stateful session bean.

Message.MsgText: MDB_MUST_IMPLEMENT_INTERFACE_CNTR0112E=CNTR0112E: The user-provided class "{0}" must implement the "{1}" interface.
Message.Explanation: The enterprise Java bean (EJB) specification requires that message-driven beans implement the message listener interface for the messaging type that it supports.
Message.UserResponse: Change the class so that it implements the interface, as required by EJB specification.

Message.MsgText: STATEFUL_TIMEOUT_ON_INTERFACE_CNTR0306W=CNTR0306W: The {0} business interface contains the @StatefulTimeout annotation. This annotation is not valid on interface types, and the Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) container ignores it.
Message.Explanation: The @StatefulTimeout annotation is only applicable on bean classes, not business interfaces. The EJB container ignores this annotations on interfaces. Unless this annotation is specified on the bean class or a bean class method, or if the bean declares a stateful-timeout in the ejb-jar.xml deployment descriptor, the bean will use a default timeout value.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the @StatefulTimeout annotation from the specified business interface, and verify that the annotations are specified correctly in the bean class.

Message.MsgText: EJB_NO_TYPE_DEFINED_CNTR0170E=CNTR0170E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module does not have a defined bean type.
Message.Explanation: Each enterprise bean must specify a bean type such as stateless session bean, message driven bean, and so on.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the Java source code annotation or the ejb-jar.xml configuration setting for this bean. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: INIT_METHOD_NOT_FOUND_CNTR0236E=CNTR0236E: The {1} enterprise bean has an init-method element, which specifies the {0} method. This method is not a public method of this bean.
Message.Explanation: The init-method element specifies a method name that is not a public method of the enterprise bean class.
Message.UserResponse: Correct either the method name or the method signature in the init-method element to specify a public method of this bean.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_ARG_RETURN_TYPE_CNTR5100E=CNTR5100E: The {0} argument or return type of the {1} method on the {2} interface is not a valid type for Remote Method Invocation over the Internet Inter-ORB Protocol (RMI/IIOP).
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the arguments and return types of all EJB remote business methods must be a valid type for RMI/IIOP.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application method to only use valid types for RMI/IIOP. Also, you can change the application to not use the interface as an EJB remote interface.

Message.MsgText: STATEFUL_TIMEOUT_WITHOUT_TIMEOUT_CNTR0308W=CNTR0308W: The {0} Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) in the {1} module of the {2} application contains the stateful-timeout deployment descriptor element, but is missing the required timeout element. The Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) container will compute a default value.
Message.Explanation: The timeout value is required to be specified on the stateful-timeout deployment descriptor element.
Message.UserResponse: Add a timeout value to the stateful-timeout deployment descriptor element for the specified bean.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_BOOLEAN_FORMAT_CNTR0120W=CNTR0120W: EJB java:comp/env context environment entry {0} of type Boolean, not set to a valid boolean value: {1}. Entry assigned a value of "false".
Message.Explanation: An enterprise Java bean (EJB) java:comp/env context environment entry of the type Boolean should be assigned a value of 'true' or 'false'. Any other value will result in 'false', but it might be an indication of a problem in the configuration. The application might not behave as expected.
Message.UserResponse: Change the EJB java:comp/env context environment entry of type Boolean to either 'true' or 'false'.

Message.MsgText: IOEXCEPTION_WRITING_FILE_FOR_STATEFUL_SESSION_BEAN_CNTR0025W=CNTR0025W: Unable to open output stream: {0} {1} {2}
Message.Explanation: The container encountered an IOException while attempting to write a file for a stateful session bean.
Message.UserResponse: See the message in the IOException to determine the action to take. Ensure that the proper file permissions are set for the file.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_MODULE_DRSSETTINGS_CNTR0095W=CNTR0095W: EJB module configuration for session bean "{0}" is missing override of memory-to-memory replication settings.
Message.Explanation: The session bean is configured to override the settings for memory-to-memory replication at the enterprise Java bean (EJB) module level, but no settings for memory-to-memory replication are provided at the EJB module level.
Message.UserResponse: Disable the override at the EJB module level, or provide the settings for memory-to-memory replication for this session bean.

Message.MsgText: JNDI_BINDING_HAS_NO_CORRESPONDING_HOME_INTERFACE_CLASS_CNTR0141E=CNTR0141E: The {0} bean in the {1} module has specified a home Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) binding. The binding does not have a matching home interface class.
Message.Explanation: Each home JNDI binding must have a matching home interface class configured.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file or source code annotations to configure a valid home interface class.

Message.MsgText: AUTOMATIC_TIMER_ON_STATEFUL_SESSION_CNTR0207E=CNTR0207E: The {0} stateful session bean in the {1} module has an automatic timer.
Message.Explanation: You cannot specify automatic timers for stateful session beans.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the automatic timer, or change the bean type.

Message.MsgText: IGNORING_UNEXPECTED_EXCEPTION_CNTR0033E=CNTR0033E: EJB container ignoring caught unexpected exception: {0}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_NOPROXY_CNTR0106E=CNTR0106E: Method {0} cannot acquire proxy for stoken = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The method that is specified was not able to obtain a proxy for processing the servant token.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: PASSIVATION_DIRECTORY_DOES_NOT_EXIST_CNTR0023W=CNTR0023W: Directory "{0}" does not exist. The EJB Container will use the current directory for passivating beans.
Message.Explanation: The container failed to open the passivation directory.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the passivation directory exists.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TYPE_IN_JAVA_COMP_ENV_CNTR0011W=CNTR0011W: An invalid type was specified for a bean''s java:comp/env context environment entry: <env-entry-name> {0}
Message.Explanation: The container encountered a type for an environment entry that is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the environment entry type is one of : String, Integer, Boolean, Double, Byte, Short, Long or Float.

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_FIND_REMOVE_BINARIES_TASK_CNTR0253W=CNTR0253W: Unable to find the RemoveBinaries task. As a result, if automatically created EJB timers exist, they are not removed.
Message.Explanation: Use the removeAutomaticEJBTimers command to manually remove any automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers that are no longer valid.
Message.UserResponse: The processing to remove any automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers is triggered by another internal process, called RemoveBinaries, which was not found. As a result, the processing to remove automatic Enterprise Java Bean timers did not run.

Message.MsgText: JIT_MISSING_ENTITYBEAN_CNTR5009E=CNTR5009E: The {1} bean class for the {0} entity bean does not implement the javax.ejb.EntityBean class.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the entity bean class must implement the javax.ejb.EntityBean class.
Message.UserResponse: Change the bean class to implement the javax.ejb.EntityBean class.

Message.MsgText: TIMEOUT_METHOD_STATIC_OR_FINAL_CNTR0166E=CNTR0166E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module implements a {2} timeout method, which is declared as static or final.
Message.Explanation: Timeout methods must not be declared as static or final.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the implementation declaration for the timeout method. Then, reinstall the application.

Message.MsgText: FINDER_COLLECTION_SCOPE_TIMEOUT_NO_TIMEOUT_CNTR0048W=CNTR0048W: Bean''s finder method "{0}" erroneously specifies a finder collection timeout scope of zero.
Message.Explanation: The finder method has a finder collection timeout scope specified, but the value is set to zero.
Message.UserResponse: Provide a value that is not zero, if a finder collection timeout scope is desired.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ENTITY_BEAN_INTERFACE_SPECIFIED_CNTR0133E=CNTR0133E: The {0} entity bean in the {1} module has an interface configured for a business, message listener, or Web service endpoint.
Message.Explanation: Entity beans cannot have any of these interface types configured.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar.xml file or source code annotation configuration settings for this bean.

Message.MsgText: CLASS_PARM_LOAD_ERROR_CNTR9263E=CNTR9263E: The {0} interface class could not be processed. The {1} method parameter class was not found.
Message.Explanation: A method parameter or a method return value class of the listed class could not be loaded.
Message.UserResponse: Check to make sure that all classes passed as method parameters, or used as method return values, on methods of the listed class are included in the input Java achive (JAR) file or enterprise archive (EAR) file, or are made available using the -cp option.

Message.MsgText: JIT_MUST_EXTEND_EJBLOCAL_CNTR5014E=CNTR5014E: The {1} interface, which has been configured as the local component interface for the {0} bean, must extend the javax.ejb.EJBLocalObject interface.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the configured local component interface must extend the javax.ejb.EJBLocalObject interface.
Message.UserResponse: Change the interface to extend the javax.ejb.EJBLocalObject interface. Also, you can change the bean configuration to not specify the interface as a local component interface.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TIMEOUT_CALLBACK_SIGNATURE_CNTR0209E=CNTR0209E: The {0} enterprise bean in the {1} module has the {2} timeout callback method that does not have the required method signature.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans specification requires that timeout callback methods have the following signature: void <METHOD>() or void <METHOD>(Timer timer)
Message.UserResponse: Correct the timeout callback method signature for this bean class.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_SL_HOME_METHOD_CNTR5022E=CNTR5022E: The {1} home interface for the {0} bean has too many methods. The {2} method is not allowed.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, a home interface for a stateless session bean must have only one method. The method must be the create method.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the method from the home interface.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_EJB_CLASS_ELEMENT_CNTR0318E=CNTR0318E: No ejb-class element was specified for the {0} bean, in the {1} module, of the {2} application.
Message.Explanation: When declaring an Enterprise JavaBean in the ejb-jar.xml file, users must provide a class name for the bean.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the ejb-jar.xml file or application source code and re-install the application.

Message.MsgText: JIT_DUPLICATE_PROPERTY_METHODS_CNTR5105E=CNTR5105E: The {0} interface is not a valid remote interface. The IDL name for the {1} method conflicts with the {2} method.
Message.Explanation: For remote interfaces, the Java Language to IDL Mapping specification states the following information: Methods that follow the JavaBeans design patterns for simple read-write properties or simple read-only properties are mapped to OMG IDL interface attributes. Both specified methods map to the same OMG IDL interface attribute. The interface is not a valid RMI/IIOP type.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application by either renaming or removing one of the conflicting methods.

Message.MsgText: NEWFILE_NAME_NOT_ALLOWED_CNTR9268E=CNTR9268E: The {0} file name is not allowed for the -newfile option.
Message.Explanation: The name specified for the -newfile option is not allowed.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure the name is not the same as the input file.

Message.MsgText: LRU_THREAD_CAUGHT_EXCEPTION_CNTR0053W=CNTR0053W: Caught an exception during LRU sweep {0} {1}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ASYNC_ON_INTERFACE_CNTR0305W=CNTR0305W: The {0} business interface contains an @Asynchronous annotation. These annotations are not valid on interface types, and the Enterprise JavaBean (EJB) container ignores them.
Message.Explanation: The @Asynchronous annotation is only applicable on bean classes, not business interfaces. The EJB container ignores these annotations on the interfaces. Unless this annotation is specified on the bean class or a bean class method, or if the methods are declared asynchronous in the ejb-jar.xml deployment descriptor, the bean methods will run synchronously.
Message.UserResponse: Remove any @Asynchronous annotation from the specified business interface, and verify that the annotations are specified correctly in the bean class.

Message.MsgText: BLANK_JNDI_BINDING_NAME_CNTR0138E=CNTR0138E: The {0} bean or home in the {1} module contains a blank string value for the Java Naming and Directory Interface (JNDI) binding name.
Message.Explanation: JNDI binding names must not contain blank strings.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the ejb-jar-bnd.xml bindings file to give this bean a valid JNDI binding name.

Message.MsgText: PROTOCOL_ERROR_IN_CONTAINER_TRANSACTION_CNTR0050E=CNTR0050E: Protocol error occurred in container transaction.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: UNABLE_TO_PASSIVATE_EJB_CNTR0005W=CNTR0005W: An enterprise bean could not be passivated: {0} {1} {2}
Message.Explanation: The container was unable to passivate an enterprise bean.
Message.UserResponse: Take action based upon the exception message in message CNTR0005W.

Message.MsgText: CNTR9413E_CONFIG_READ_FAIL=CNTR9413E: Failed to read in the configuration file from {0}
Message.Explanation: The embeddable Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) container failed to read the configuration properties from the specified file. This can occur if the file is not a properly formed properties file.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the specified file exists on the file system and that it is a well formed properties file (i.e. <property_name>=<property_value>).

Message.MsgText: WS_ENDPOINT_METHOD_MISSING_CNTR0178E=CNTR0178E: Configured Web service endpoint method {0} is not implemented by the {1} bean in the {2} module of the {3} application.
Message.Explanation: All configured Web service endpoint methods must be implemented by the bean.
Message.UserResponse: Change bean implementation to include all Web service endpoint methods.

Message.MsgText: JIT_INVALID_FINALIZE_MTHD_CNTR5008E=CNTR5008E: The {1} bean class for the {0} bean has defined the finalize method.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the bean class must not define the finalize method.
Message.UserResponse: Do not define the finalize method in the bean class.

Message.MsgText: FINDER_CAUGHT_EXCEPTION_CNTR0040E=CNTR0040E: Finder failure as a result of exception {0}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: SFB_CONTROLLER_VALUEBYTES_CNTR0110E=CNTR0110E: Method {0} cannot convert value to byte array.
Message.Explanation: The method that is specified was not able to convert the passed entryKey value to a byte array.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_INTERCEPTOR_METHOD_MODIFIER_CNTR0229E=CNTR0229E: The {0} interceptor method must not be declared as final or static.
Message.Explanation: The Enterprise JavaBeans 3.0 specification does not allow an interceptor method to be final or static.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the final or static modifier from this interceptor method.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MAX_POOLSIZE_CNTR0058W=CNTR0058W: Maximum pool size specified for bean {0} not a valid integer: {1}. Default used instead.
Message.Explanation: Only a positive integer can be specified for the maximum pool size. The default value will be used.
Message.UserResponse: Change the value of the maximum pool size to a positive integer.

Message.MsgText: LIGHTWEIGHT_ENABLED_CNTR0118I=CNTR0118I: Container pre- and post-method processing for all local and local home methods will be bypassed on bean: "{0}".
Message.Explanation: The bean has been configured to streamline the processing that occurs before and after calling the methods that are defined on the local home interface and local business interface. This behavior is not compliant with the enterprise Java bean (EJB) V2.0 and later specifications, but it can improve performance.
Message.UserResponse: There is no user action required.

Message.MsgText: JIT_NOT_TOP_LEVEL_CLASS_CNTR5006E=CNTR5006E: The {1} bean class for the {0} bean is not defined as a top level class.
Message.Explanation: According to the Enterprise JavaBeans (EJB) specification, the bean class must be defined as a top level class.
Message.UserResponse: Define the bean class as a top level class.

Message.MsgText: UNEXPECTED_EXCEPTION_CNTR9258E=CNTR9258E: An unexpected exception was caught. The exception is: {0}
Message.Explanation: An unexpected exception occurred during command processing.
Message.UserResponse: Add the -verbose option to the createEJBStubs command invocation see more information.
